WEBVTT

00:00.440 --> 00:06.240
[♪♪♪]

00:07.640 --> 00:27.680
[♪♪♪]

00:28.040 --> 00:48.080
[♪♪♪]

00:48.080 --> 01:08.080
[♪♪♪]

01:08.080 --> 01:19.120
[♪♪♪]

01:19.120 --> 01:22.120
[grunting]

01:26.560 --> 01:27.840
Annabel!

01:27.840 --> 01:29.120
Crab cage coming up!

01:29.120 --> 01:30.000
[chuckling]

01:30.000 --> 01:31.440
On it, gramps!

01:31.440 --> 01:39.320
[♪♪♪]

01:39.320 --> 01:40.320
Your back.

01:40.320 --> 01:41.840
Oh, I'm fine.

01:41.840 --> 01:44.160
How much time do you think
we have?

01:44.160 --> 01:45.280
About a few more hours.

01:45.280 --> 01:47.880
We still owe Mr. Dodds money
on the booth.

01:47.880 --> 01:50.160
Everybody owes Dodds money.

01:50.160 --> 01:51.840
Hold in!

01:51.840 --> 01:53.200
[grunting]

01:53.200 --> 01:54.480
He can wait.

01:54.480 --> 01:56.840
Ugh, he will not be happy.

01:56.840 --> 01:59.760
Uh, well, in my experience,

01:59.760 --> 02:01.320
rich people usually aren't.

02:01.320 --> 02:02.600
[grunting]

02:02.600 --> 02:05.080
It is the curse
of the bourgeois classes.

02:05.080 --> 02:06.080
[sighing]

02:06.080 --> 02:08.480
So you keep telling me.

02:08.480 --> 02:11.080
You know, what I hear makes
some people happy?

02:11.080 --> 02:12.600
A special lady friend.

02:12.600 --> 02:13.720
Anna.

02:13.720 --> 02:16.040
[chuckling]

02:16.040 --> 02:17.080
[sighing]

02:17.080 --> 02:18.200
You know what?

02:18.200 --> 02:19.800
I've had
enough special lady friends

02:19.800 --> 02:22.360
to last a life time.

02:22.360 --> 02:24.800
Your grandmother was
a very special lady friend,

02:24.800 --> 02:25.800
God rest her soul.

02:25.800 --> 02:26.800
[chuckling]

02:26.800 --> 02:28.360
As was my previous wife,

02:28.360 --> 02:31.400
who now lives in my old house
with her special friend.

02:33.800 --> 02:35.640
You know, to be happy--

02:35.640 --> 02:38.800
♪ All I need is a tall ship ♪

02:38.800 --> 02:41.400
♪ And a star to sail her by ♪

02:41.400 --> 02:42.520
Ugh!

02:42.520 --> 02:43.480
Oh!

02:43.480 --> 02:44.360
Please, stop.

02:44.360 --> 02:45.480
[laughing]

02:45.480 --> 02:48.360
And I need a first mate
to clean the crab cages.

02:48.360 --> 02:49.640
[sighing]

02:49.640 --> 02:52.080
I think the captain is supposed
to clean the crab cages

02:52.080 --> 02:55.080
while the first mate relaxes
in the sun.

02:55.080 --> 02:56.520
[laughing]

02:56.520 --> 02:57.960
That would be mutiny!

02:57.960 --> 02:58.920
[chuckling]

02:58.920 --> 03:00.600
Not if you stop singing.

03:00.600 --> 03:02.720
Come on, let's get back to work.

03:04.120 --> 03:24.160
[♪♪♪]

03:24.160 --> 03:39.120
[♪♪♪]

03:39.120 --> 03:41.560
Alright, it's spread away
and ready to go.

03:41.560 --> 03:44.280
Anna?

03:44.280 --> 03:46.280
Annabel?

03:48.880 --> 03:50.400
[laughing]

03:50.400 --> 04:00.560
[♪♪♪]

04:00.560 --> 04:02.480
Good morning, Mitzy!

04:05.360 --> 04:07.160
[laughing]

04:07.160 --> 04:27.160
[♪♪♪]

04:30.440 --> 04:31.800
Go for it, Mitzy!

04:36.160 --> 04:38.720
[laughing]

04:38.720 --> 04:47.520
[♪♪♪]

04:47.520 --> 04:49.400
Mitzy's in a good mood today.

04:49.400 --> 04:50.760
That's because it's a good day.

04:50.760 --> 04:52.520
[chuckling]

04:52.520 --> 04:53.400
You know what?

04:53.400 --> 04:54.960
Every day is a good day.

04:54.960 --> 04:55.800
[chuckling]

04:55.800 --> 04:57.760
As long as I have my two girls.

04:57.760 --> 04:58.720
Is that right, Mitzy?

05:02.360 --> 05:04.040
Come on.

05:06.600 --> 05:26.640
[♪♪♪]

05:26.640 --> 05:46.640
[♪♪♪]

05:46.640 --> 06:06.680
[♪♪♪]

06:06.680 --> 06:13.120
[♪♪♪]

06:13.120 --> 06:15.440
Hey, Arthur,
can you take my line?

06:15.440 --> 06:17.000
Sure, Jonah, no problem.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.160
How's the fishing?

06:18.160 --> 06:19.600
I ain't caught none yet.

06:19.600 --> 06:20.560
[Jonah chuckling]

06:20.560 --> 06:22.280
[Jonah]
Around the green pole is fine.

06:23.440 --> 06:25.200
[Jonah sighing]

06:25.200 --> 06:26.920
Right.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.280
[grunting]

06:28.280 --> 06:29.760
Okay, buddy,
how you doin' today?

06:29.760 --> 06:31.040
I'm happy.

06:31.040 --> 06:33.440
[laughing]

06:33.440 --> 06:34.600
[Jonah grunting]

06:34.600 --> 06:35.880
-Hey, Will, this one's heavy.
-Yes, sir.

06:35.880 --> 06:37.040
-How you doing, Grace?
-I'm Good, Jonah.

06:37.040 --> 06:38.720
-How are you?
-[Jonah] Going well.

06:38.720 --> 06:40.760
[Mrs. Johnson]
Alright.

06:40.760 --> 06:41.640
[grunting]

06:41.640 --> 06:43.280
You guys out late this morning.

06:43.280 --> 06:45.120
Good fishing?

06:45.120 --> 06:46.120
It was pretty good, Grace.

06:46.120 --> 06:47.040
[grunting]

06:47.040 --> 06:48.360
Here, I'll show you.

06:48.360 --> 06:49.480
Alright.

06:49.480 --> 06:51.880
[grunting]

06:51.880 --> 06:52.520
[Jonah]
Thanks, buddy.

06:52.520 --> 06:55.200
Thanks for your help.

06:55.200 --> 06:57.320
-[Jonah] What about--
-Mmm.

06:57.320 --> 06:58.880
-[Jonah] This guy, huh?
-[Mrs. Johnson] Nice, nice.

06:58.880 --> 07:00.080
[Jonah chuckling]

07:02.240 --> 07:03.320
[Will]
Oh!

07:03.320 --> 07:04.480
Will you leave that fish alone?

07:04.480 --> 07:06.040
Come and take these crabs
to the restaurant.

07:06.040 --> 07:07.160
[Will]
Yes, auntie.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.800
I finished that book
you lent me, Mr. Coleridge.

07:10.800 --> 07:12.040
Oh, that's great, Will!

07:12.040 --> 07:13.160
Listen, anytime you want a book,

07:13.160 --> 07:14.240
there's plenty more
where that came from.

07:14.240 --> 07:15.200
Oh, cool.

07:15.200 --> 07:16.320
Didn't I tell you to get going?

07:16.320 --> 07:18.040
Oh.

07:18.040 --> 07:18.880
Thank you.

07:18.880 --> 07:19.800
Hurry, just--

07:19.800 --> 07:21.360
[chuckling]

07:21.360 --> 07:23.320
[sighing]

07:23.320 --> 07:24.480
Oh, Jonah, no.

07:24.480 --> 07:25.760
I'll let Will come help you
with that.

07:25.760 --> 07:28.360
Grace, I'm not so old man
that I can't carry my own fish.

07:28.360 --> 07:30.640
Fine then,
break your old fool neck.

07:30.640 --> 07:32.280
Don't mean a thing to me.

07:32.280 --> 07:33.280
Come on, Annabel.

07:33.280 --> 07:34.760
[Annabel]
Alright.

07:34.760 --> 07:35.920
Bye, Annabel.

07:35.920 --> 07:38.080
Bye, Ms. Johnson.

07:38.080 --> 07:39.800
[Jonah]
Alright, girl.

07:39.800 --> 07:41.120
[chuckles]

07:41.120 --> 07:42.400
-Morning!
-Good morning!

07:42.400 --> 07:43.400
Good morning, good morning,
good morning!

07:43.400 --> 07:44.360
How you all doin'?

07:44.360 --> 07:46.240
Hi, Mr. Ragsdale.

07:47.960 --> 07:49.360
Hello, birdie girl.

07:49.360 --> 07:50.560
Hi, birdie guy.

07:50.560 --> 07:51.840
Hello.

07:51.840 --> 07:52.840
Hello.

07:54.240 --> 07:55.280
Hi, Mr. Jenks.

07:55.280 --> 07:56.720
Any new jokes today?

07:56.720 --> 07:59.280
Well, let me think.

07:59.280 --> 08:02.200
Where do fish keep their money?

08:02.200 --> 08:03.440
In a river bank.

08:03.440 --> 08:05.120
Oh man.

08:05.120 --> 08:06.240
Alright.

08:06.240 --> 08:08.120
What made the fish blush?

08:08.120 --> 08:09.840
'Cause he saw
the ocean's bottom.

08:09.840 --> 08:11.800
Man, you know them all, girl!

08:11.800 --> 08:13.120
[chuckling]

08:13.120 --> 08:15.840
[Jenkins]
Okay.

08:15.840 --> 08:16.800
Oh, you know what?

08:16.800 --> 08:18.280
I'm gonna need some more ice.

08:18.280 --> 08:19.160
Okay.

08:19.160 --> 08:20.520
-See you in a minute.
-Okay.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.600
Hi, Mitzy.

08:24.600 --> 08:26.040
[chuckling]

08:26.040 --> 08:27.560
Thank you.

08:27.560 --> 08:30.400
Do you know
any good dolphin jokes?

08:30.400 --> 08:31.600
[chuckling]

08:31.600 --> 08:33.600
[Annabel]
That's because there aren't any.

08:33.600 --> 08:52.360
[♪♪♪]

08:52.360 --> 08:54.320
[sighing]

08:56.560 --> 08:58.360
Hey, Annabel!

08:58.360 --> 09:01.280
What do you get when you cross
a messy room

09:01.280 --> 09:02.440
with a crawfish?

09:02.440 --> 09:03.720
What?

09:03.720 --> 09:06.600
A slobster.

09:06.600 --> 09:07.440
Oh my God!

09:07.440 --> 09:10.440
[Jonah laughing]

09:10.440 --> 09:12.040
God!

09:12.040 --> 09:14.600
She did that on purpose!

09:14.600 --> 09:17.040
Mitzy is an impeccable judge
of both humor

09:17.040 --> 09:18.640
and character.

09:18.640 --> 09:20.760
This is true.

09:20.760 --> 09:22.360
Come on, girl.

09:22.360 --> 09:24.520
Bye, Mitzy.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.000
[chuckling]

09:26.000 --> 09:27.640
[Jonah grunting]

09:31.800 --> 09:33.760
How's your homework?

09:33.760 --> 09:36.760
Did you give in that essay
on Alexander the Great?

09:36.760 --> 09:37.760
Yeah, I did.

09:37.760 --> 09:39.920
The teacher said
it was kind of long.

09:39.920 --> 09:40.920
No.

09:40.920 --> 09:42.240
[sighs]

09:42.240 --> 09:45.240
History is how we know
who we are

09:45.240 --> 09:47.240
and where we're going.

09:47.240 --> 09:48.200
It defines us.

09:48.200 --> 09:50.120
It enlightens us.

09:50.120 --> 09:52.640
How can you have
too much history?

09:52.640 --> 09:54.240
Apparently,
when you help me write it.

09:54.240 --> 09:55.800
Oh.

09:55.800 --> 09:57.480
Well, is there anything else
I can help you with?

09:57.480 --> 09:58.720
Math.

09:58.720 --> 09:59.680
[laughing]

09:59.680 --> 10:00.800
You're on your own.

10:00.800 --> 10:03.120
[laughing]

10:04.840 --> 10:07.840
[indistinct chatter]

10:07.840 --> 10:27.840
[♪♪♪]

10:27.840 --> 10:41.120
[♪♪♪]

10:41.120 --> 10:42.440
[James]
Hey, Jonah?

10:42.440 --> 10:44.280
James, my old friend,

10:44.280 --> 10:47.280
I have the best and freshest stone crab

10:47.280 --> 10:49.840
on the island.

10:49.840 --> 10:51.480
Seriously.

10:51.480 --> 10:54.480
Between you and I,
it would be a culinary crime

10:55.720 --> 10:58.720
if a less skilled chef
than yourself were to walk by

10:58.720 --> 11:00.840
and deprive your hotel's guests
of these

11:00.840 --> 11:02.720
decapod delicacies.

11:02.720 --> 11:05.560
Oh, 8 a pound.

11:05.560 --> 11:07.120
James, I am shocked.

11:07.120 --> 11:08.400
Shocked!

11:08.400 --> 11:10.400
After all the years
I've known you,

11:10.400 --> 11:13.320
that the food should be taken
out of my granddaughter's mouth

11:14.320 --> 11:16.440
by a man who I consider
to be a friend,

11:16.440 --> 11:18.280
nay, a brother.

11:18.280 --> 11:20.160
Okay, you lil' pirates.

11:20.160 --> 11:21.880
-9 a pound.
-10.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.880
And we'll throw in
these fresh conch.

11:23.880 --> 11:25.000
[sighing]

11:25.000 --> 11:25.880
Deal.

11:25.880 --> 11:27.880
[chuckling]

11:27.880 --> 11:29.480
Alright, here you go.

11:29.480 --> 11:31.320
Thank you.

11:34.360 --> 11:35.800
How are things at the center?

11:35.800 --> 11:38.040
Oh, they're okay.

11:38.040 --> 11:40.160
You know, business is down
since the hurricane.

11:40.160 --> 11:41.480
[scoffs]

11:41.480 --> 11:44.160
When my son called
it a "non-profit", he meant it.

11:44.160 --> 11:45.800
Your boy sure loved that place.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.360
Hmm, yes.

11:47.360 --> 11:49.040
He did.

11:49.040 --> 11:50.040
Annabel, time for school.

11:50.040 --> 11:51.600
Oh, okay.

11:55.920 --> 11:58.920
[indistinct conversation
in distance]

12:00.640 --> 12:03.480
So I usually don't go
for the blue.

12:03.480 --> 12:04.480
[Candice's mother]
Mmhmm.

12:04.480 --> 12:07.480
[indistinct conversation]

12:12.320 --> 12:13.640
I do want to get one more.

12:13.640 --> 12:14.840
Okay.

12:14.840 --> 12:17.400
I've got um,
these short earrings

12:17.400 --> 12:19.040
that I'm really partial to.

12:19.040 --> 12:20.480
I think you might wanna see it.

12:20.480 --> 12:22.480
And um, some more bracelets.

12:22.480 --> 12:23.680
[Tourist's wife]
Oh yeah.

12:23.680 --> 12:26.680
[indistinct speech]

12:31.200 --> 12:33.120
Excuse me, sir, but I think
you dropped your wallet.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.240
Hey, that's my wallet.

12:34.240 --> 12:36.640
It has all my money in it.

12:36.640 --> 12:38.240
It's all there.

12:38.240 --> 12:40.240
What a nice island boy, honey.

12:40.240 --> 12:41.800
Give him a reward.

12:44.280 --> 12:47.280
[indistinct conversation
in background]

12:51.560 --> 12:53.520
[Tourist's wife]
That's amazing.

12:53.520 --> 12:55.600
Oh, I like it in silver, too.

12:55.600 --> 12:58.000
[inaudible]

12:58.000 --> 13:00.320
[indistinct conversation
in background]

13:00.320 --> 13:03.280
[sighs]

13:03.280 --> 13:04.520
[Tourist's wife]
I'll have that other bracelet--

13:04.520 --> 13:06.560
[indistinct speech]

13:06.560 --> 13:10.160
I'm sorry, sir, but I couldn't
possibly take your money.

13:10.160 --> 13:12.160
Please enjoy your time
on the island.

13:13.160 --> 13:15.000
Thanks, kid.

13:15.000 --> 13:22.520
[♪♪♪]

13:22.520 --> 13:24.240
Duh.

13:24.240 --> 13:44.280
[♪♪♪]

13:51.640 --> 13:53.320
$100.

13:53.320 --> 13:55.320
Excuse me?

13:57.320 --> 13:58.440
I said--

13:58.440 --> 14:00.600
[grunts]

14:00.600 --> 14:02.320
$100.

14:02.320 --> 14:03.800
$100 for what?

14:03.800 --> 14:05.440
Well, I you wanna go
on a fishing trip,

14:05.440 --> 14:07.440
it's $100 an hour.

14:07.440 --> 14:08.960
I supply reels for fly-fishing,

14:08.960 --> 14:10.760
but you bring your own rig
for big game,

14:10.760 --> 14:13.200
and there is no smoking
and no drinking on the boat.

14:13.200 --> 14:14.320
[chuckles]

14:14.320 --> 14:16.800
Well, I don't drink or smoke.

14:16.800 --> 14:17.960
Or fish.

14:17.960 --> 14:19.760
Well, then what are you doing
on my boat?

14:19.760 --> 14:21.920
I'm lookin'
for Jonah Coleridge.

14:21.920 --> 14:23.520
Oh, well, that's a coincidence!

14:23.520 --> 14:25.920
I'm looking at someone
who is trespassing on my boat

14:25.920 --> 14:28.600
on a private deck.

14:28.600 --> 14:30.240
My name is Desaray Rolle.

14:30.240 --> 14:32.640
I work for the Freeport
Social Services Department.

14:32.640 --> 14:35.200
[grunting]

14:35.200 --> 14:37.640
And I was led to understand
that there was a Jonah Coleridge

14:37.640 --> 14:38.760
who lived here
with his granddaughter.

14:38.760 --> 14:40.360
Excuse me!

14:40.360 --> 14:42.840
[grunting]

14:44.200 --> 14:45.640
What happened to Nole?

14:45.640 --> 14:47.840
Uh, Mr. Lewis retired.

14:47.840 --> 14:50.120
They sent me here from Nassau
to take over his cases.

14:50.120 --> 14:51.960
Oh, that's too bad.

14:51.960 --> 14:53.360
I liked Nole.

14:53.360 --> 14:55.720
He couldn't fish worth a fart,
but he was good company.

14:55.720 --> 14:58.680
So am I to assume
that you are Jonah Coleridge?

14:58.680 --> 15:01.320
Well, you may assume
whatever you like.

15:01.320 --> 15:02.240
[grunting]

15:02.240 --> 15:05.240
Personally,
I try to avoid

15:05.240 --> 15:08.280
conclusions before investigation,

15:08.280 --> 15:10.280
but you may do as you wish.

15:10.280 --> 15:12.080
Is that supposed to be clever?

15:12.080 --> 15:13.120
Yes.

15:13.120 --> 15:14.560
Sir, I do not have time
for your games.

15:14.560 --> 15:16.560
Are you or are you not
Jonah Coleridge?

15:16.560 --> 15:17.800
I am.

15:17.800 --> 15:20.800
Then why didn't you say so?

15:20.800 --> 15:23.800
Because I don't like people
snooping around

15:23.800 --> 15:26.840
my home before they have

15:26.840 --> 15:29.280
the courtesy to ask
for an invitation.

15:30.400 --> 15:32.160
I am here to examine

15:32.160 --> 15:34.280
the living situation
of the minor

15:34.280 --> 15:36.120
who is in your care,
Mr. Coleridge.

15:36.120 --> 15:38.440
Oh, I'm not questioning
your career choices, Miss Rolle,

15:38.440 --> 15:39.880
only your manners.

15:39.880 --> 15:41.120
Hmm.

15:41.120 --> 15:43.120
Is this boat yours'
and Annabel's primary place

15:43.120 --> 15:44.120
of residency?

15:44.120 --> 15:45.280
It is.

15:45.280 --> 15:47.560
And where is Annabel?

15:47.560 --> 15:49.720
Well, where would you expect her
to be at this time?

15:49.720 --> 15:50.600
[Desaray]
Hmm.

15:50.600 --> 15:52.680
She's coming home from school.

15:55.160 --> 15:57.000
Okay.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.560
Bye, Megan.

15:59.560 --> 16:02.440
[indistinct chatter in distance]

16:02.440 --> 16:22.480
[♪♪♪]

16:22.480 --> 16:42.480
[♪♪♪]

16:42.480 --> 17:02.520
[♪♪♪]

17:04.680 --> 17:06.120
[grunts]

17:06.120 --> 17:09.120
Who are you and why have
you been following me?

17:09.120 --> 17:11.520
I am Robert M. Carbunkle.

17:11.520 --> 17:14.520
My card.

17:14.520 --> 17:15.920
You're a barista?

17:15.920 --> 17:17.760
That says "barrister".

17:17.760 --> 17:19.120
There's an R at the end.

17:19.120 --> 17:20.160
You don't look like a lawyer.

17:20.160 --> 17:21.400
You look more like a pirate.

17:21.400 --> 17:22.920
I have a suit.

17:22.920 --> 17:24.120
Look can I get up?

17:24.120 --> 17:27.120
I don't feel like lounging
in dead fish.

17:27.120 --> 17:29.000
Just don't try anything funny.

17:29.000 --> 17:32.000
I assure you the last thing
I'm trying to be is funny.

17:38.840 --> 17:39.960
[grunting]

17:39.960 --> 17:41.360
I am working--

17:41.360 --> 17:43.840
[grunting]

17:43.840 --> 17:45.080
I'm working
for your grandparents

17:45.080 --> 17:46.120
on your mother's side.

17:46.120 --> 17:47.960
Samuel and Sheryl Williams.

17:47.960 --> 17:49.240
I haven't seen them in--

17:49.240 --> 17:50.720
Nearly 10 years.

17:50.720 --> 17:53.720
They hired me
to give this to you.

17:53.720 --> 17:56.720
That letter
will explain everything.

17:56.720 --> 17:58.520
And if you are amenable,

17:58.520 --> 18:00.000
call me on the number
on my card,

18:00.000 --> 18:01.680
then I'll arrange everything.

18:01.680 --> 18:03.720
Good day.

18:07.840 --> 18:09.600
Bye.

18:11.880 --> 18:14.320
So this place is
a research center?

18:15.320 --> 18:17.400
Well, it's a non-profit
marine research

18:17.400 --> 18:19.760
and conservation center.

18:19.760 --> 18:21.840
My son was a marine biologist.

18:21.840 --> 18:23.200
[sighs]

18:23.200 --> 18:26.200
He came out to the island,
fresh out of grad school,

18:26.200 --> 18:28.880
and fell in love with the place.

18:28.880 --> 18:31.880
He founded the center,
and then he ran it by himself,

18:33.560 --> 18:34.920
and Debrah joined him later.

18:34.920 --> 18:37.760
Until they died, 10 years ago?

18:37.760 --> 18:39.920
Yes.

18:39.920 --> 18:42.160
And now, you own it?

18:42.160 --> 18:44.000
Well, in theory, Anna does.

18:45.600 --> 18:46.880
Oh, the staff run the center,

18:46.880 --> 18:48.720
but Anna helps
with the dolphins.

18:48.720 --> 18:50.920
[Jonah]
There's one in particular,
she's very fond of.

18:50.920 --> 18:52.920
Hmm, that's nice.

18:52.920 --> 18:54.200
Well, yes, it is actually.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.480
[Desaray]
And these people--

18:56.480 --> 18:59.480
They live here I assume.

18:59.480 --> 19:02.320
Well, just my son's friends.

19:02.320 --> 19:03.440
Well,
he said they could stay here

19:03.440 --> 19:04.800
and I saw no reason
to change matters.

19:04.800 --> 19:07.240
Your son sounds like
a very interesting person.

19:08.320 --> 19:10.240
He was the best man
I ever knew.

19:10.240 --> 19:12.800
Do you make your living
as a fisherman then?

19:12.800 --> 19:13.920
Yeah.

19:13.920 --> 19:16.360
I also do chartered fishing
and diving tours.

19:16.360 --> 19:17.960
And there's my pension.

19:17.960 --> 19:19.160
Hmm.

19:19.160 --> 19:20.640
Thank you, Mr. Coleridge.

19:20.640 --> 19:22.360
I think
I understand the situation.

19:22.360 --> 19:25.240
What situation is that,
precisely?

19:25.240 --> 19:27.760
It will be in my report.

19:27.760 --> 19:29.480
Do you have problems
expressing your opinions

19:29.480 --> 19:31.960
to peoples' faces, Mrs. Rolle?

19:31.960 --> 19:34.840
Or are you more comfortable
hiding behind reports?

19:34.840 --> 19:36.280
I'm very comfortable

19:36.280 --> 19:39.280
sharing my opinion,
Mr. Coleridge.

19:40.360 --> 19:41.800
Annabel, by all accounts,

19:41.800 --> 19:44.800
is a smart
and hard-working young lady

19:44.800 --> 19:47.800
who has suffered
a terrible tragedy.

19:47.800 --> 19:50.400
And, instead of accepting
your responsibility

19:50.400 --> 19:53.000
to raise her in a safe
and nurturing environment,

19:54.000 --> 19:55.680
you took advantage
of the situation

19:55.680 --> 19:58.440
to retire to a paradise,

19:58.440 --> 20:00.400
play Popeye the Sailor Man
and drink rumrunners

20:00.400 --> 20:03.400
with your friends all day.

20:03.400 --> 20:05.960
You don't know
what you are talking about.

20:05.960 --> 20:07.400
-This is good place to live.
-Hmm.

20:07.400 --> 20:08.640
There are some fine people here.

20:08.640 --> 20:09.920
[Annabel]
Where is grandpa!

20:12.000 --> 20:14.000
Not now, Mitzy.

20:14.000 --> 20:15.560
Grandpa!

20:15.560 --> 20:18.000
Oh, just wait until I tell you
about my way over--

20:18.000 --> 20:19.520
Uh, oh-- hello.

20:19.520 --> 20:22.520
Hello, you must be Annabel.

20:22.520 --> 20:25.000
Um, Annabel, this is Mrs. Rolle
from Social Services.

20:26.120 --> 20:27.880
She's come here to judge us.

20:27.880 --> 20:30.000
What do you have there, Annabel?

20:30.000 --> 20:32.720
Oh, a letter I got
from a strange man.

20:32.720 --> 20:35.720
Anna, how many times have I told
about talking to strangers?

20:35.720 --> 20:38.320
I only talked to him
after I hit him with an oar.

20:38.320 --> 20:40.440
Did he try and harm you?

20:40.440 --> 20:43.000
Uh, no,
he just took photos of me.

20:43.000 --> 20:45.560
He looked like a pirate,
but he was just a lawyer.

20:45.560 --> 20:46.560
Wait.

20:46.560 --> 20:48.880
Uh,
a lawyer gave you this letter?

20:48.880 --> 20:50.760
Yeah, I thought it was
another bill collector.

20:50.760 --> 20:52.840
Oh you have a lot of
late bills?

20:52.840 --> 20:53.880
[Annabel]
Oh, yes.

20:53.880 --> 20:55.280
That's how
we keep the bourgeois class

20:55.280 --> 20:56.600
at our mercy.

20:58.720 --> 21:01.280
Uh, Mrs. Rolle,
we'll have to finish this later.

21:01.280 --> 21:02.320
Well, actually,

21:02.320 --> 21:04.320
I haven't finished my interview
with Annabel.

21:04.320 --> 21:05.720
No, I must insist.

21:05.720 --> 21:07.040
I'm sorry.

21:07.040 --> 21:08.040
Please, excuse us.

21:11.040 --> 21:13.760
Annabel, I will see you soon.

21:13.760 --> 21:14.600
Oh, okay.

21:14.600 --> 21:16.920
Bye!

21:16.920 --> 21:19.160
What was that all about, gramps?

21:19.160 --> 21:20.520
Hmm?

21:20.520 --> 21:23.360
Oh, it's uh, nothing.

21:23.360 --> 21:24.480
[sighs]

21:24.480 --> 21:27.360
Well, I wish you'd
chosen another day

21:27.360 --> 21:28.920
to assault someone.

21:28.920 --> 21:30.760
He was a lawyer, gramps.

21:30.760 --> 21:33.080
Oh, well, that's alright then.

21:33.080 --> 21:34.760
You hungry?

21:39.240 --> 21:42.240
[indistinct lyrics]

21:42.240 --> 21:44.800
You don't seem happy
about the letter.

21:44.800 --> 21:46.680
Well, it's not that.

21:46.680 --> 21:47.920
It's just that I haven't heard
a word

21:47.920 --> 21:49.080
from your grandparents

21:49.080 --> 21:51.080
since we held memorial service
for your mum and dad.

21:51.080 --> 21:53.400
Why would they suddenly want
to see us now?

21:53.400 --> 21:56.080
Don't you like them?

21:56.080 --> 21:57.080
Well, we have
a difficult relationship.

21:57.080 --> 21:58.200
[Mrs. Johnson scoffs]

21:58.200 --> 21:59.320
[Mrs. Johnson]
Ain't that the truth.

21:59.320 --> 22:01.360
You know, the last time
that your grandfather saw

22:01.360 --> 22:02.960
that weasely little city man,

22:02.960 --> 22:04.120
he punched him straight
in the nose.

22:04.120 --> 22:05.520
[Jonah]
Uh, Grace.

22:05.520 --> 22:06.560
What?

22:06.560 --> 22:08.080
He had it comin'
and you know it.

22:08.080 --> 22:10.240
[Mrs. Johnson]
That fancy good-for-nothin' man
strutting around here

22:10.240 --> 22:12.120
with all his airs and money

22:12.120 --> 22:13.920
tellin' everyone
how things supposed to be.

22:13.920 --> 22:15.920
Now, his wife you know,
she was nice enough,

22:15.920 --> 22:17.000
but that man,

22:17.000 --> 22:18.800
if your granddad hadn't hit him,
I would have.

22:18.800 --> 22:19.800
Trust me.

22:19.800 --> 22:21.960
Grace, I think she's got it now.

22:21.960 --> 22:23.680
Oh, okay, fine.

22:23.680 --> 22:25.400
You don't want me
tellin' the girl,

22:25.400 --> 22:26.840
you won't hear a word about it.

22:26.840 --> 22:29.520
And it's not like I don't know
where I'm not wanted.

22:29.520 --> 22:31.600
Ooh.

22:31.600 --> 22:34.080
So what was the arguing about?

22:35.560 --> 22:37.600
Nothing.

22:37.600 --> 22:40.000
Oh, just a disagreement.

22:40.000 --> 22:42.120
It was a very difficult time.

22:42.120 --> 22:44.120
Maybe they wanna make up?

22:44.120 --> 22:45.440
[sighs]

22:45.440 --> 22:47.000
Annabel, give me your hand.

22:49.320 --> 22:52.280
Do you want to see them?

22:52.280 --> 22:54.720
Well, they are my family.

22:54.720 --> 22:55.840
Right.

22:55.840 --> 22:58.400
Then I'll call the lawyer,
we'll have lunch.

22:58.400 --> 23:00.400
-Okay?
-Thank you!

23:00.400 --> 23:03.400
[indistinct lyrics]

23:03.400 --> 23:11.560
[♪♪♪]

23:13.160 --> 23:15.760
Zoe, get over here
with that ice cream.

23:16.760 --> 23:17.520
Keep these comin'.

23:17.520 --> 23:18.640
I had a rough day

23:18.640 --> 23:20.720
and I'm eating my feelings,
obviously.

23:20.720 --> 23:22.320
Okay.

23:28.320 --> 23:29.600
Yeah.

23:29.600 --> 23:31.760
Oh, Mr. Williams, sir.

23:31.760 --> 23:33.600
Yes, sir, I am just
at the office right now

23:33.600 --> 23:35.640
I was just going over
your files here

23:35.640 --> 23:37.480
How was your flight, sir?

23:37.480 --> 23:39.600
Oh,
I'm sorry to hear that, sir.

23:39.600 --> 23:42.440
Yep, we call that
"island time", sir.

23:42.440 --> 23:44.760
People here uh,
have a different relationship

23:44.760 --> 23:46.200
to time than--

23:46.200 --> 23:47.800
Uh, oh, no, sir.

23:47.800 --> 23:48.920
No, you're absolutely right.

23:48.920 --> 23:50.520
They should have--

23:50.520 --> 23:52.680
Yes, sir, uh, of course.

23:52.680 --> 23:54.240
No, sir-- I mean, yes, sir.

23:54.240 --> 23:55.240
Yes.

23:55.240 --> 23:56.480
No, I've arranged all of that.

23:56.480 --> 23:58.760
We're having lunch with them
at your hotel, sir.

23:58.760 --> 23:59.800
Yes.

23:59.800 --> 24:01.320
And may I just say, sir,
that I really appreciate

24:01.320 --> 24:03.800
the opportunity
to be working uh--

24:03.800 --> 24:05.080
Sir?

24:05.080 --> 24:06.520
Mr. Williams, sir?

24:08.480 --> 24:09.760
Jerk.

24:14.920 --> 24:34.960
[♪♪♪]

24:36.800 --> 24:37.520
Grandma!

24:37.520 --> 24:39.360
Grandpa!

24:39.360 --> 24:40.360
[chuckling]

24:40.360 --> 24:43.200
Oh, Annabel, look at you.

24:43.200 --> 24:44.360
You're so beautiful.

24:44.360 --> 24:46.240
Samuel,
look at how beautiful she is.

24:46.240 --> 24:48.240
She's a vision, Sheryl.

24:48.240 --> 24:49.320
An absolute vision.

24:49.320 --> 24:50.600
Sheryl.

24:50.600 --> 24:52.400
Sam.

24:58.280 --> 25:00.120
This is Mr. Carbunkle.

25:00.120 --> 25:01.520
Oh, gramps, that's the lawyer.

25:01.520 --> 25:02.680
Ah!

25:02.680 --> 25:04.600
The man you payed
to stalk my granddaughter.

25:04.600 --> 25:06.720
Mr. Carbunkle is
a local barrister.

25:06.720 --> 25:08.680
He was recommended by my firm
in New York

25:08.680 --> 25:10.720
to assist us in this matter.

25:10.720 --> 25:13.240
What is that you want,
Mr. Williams?

25:15.280 --> 25:17.960
[exhales]

25:17.960 --> 25:19.040
Sheryl and I think it's time
to--

25:19.040 --> 25:21.600
Anna, dear, how would you
like

25:21.600 --> 25:23.560
to visit New York?

25:23.560 --> 25:24.400
Really?

25:24.400 --> 25:25.280
Wow, that would be awesome!

25:25.280 --> 25:26.160
[Annabel]
Just--

25:26.160 --> 25:27.280
I can't stay too long.

25:27.280 --> 25:29.840
You know, I have the center uh,
and school--

25:29.840 --> 25:30.880
Mmhmm.

25:30.880 --> 25:32.880
-And Mitzy, of course.
-Uh, who is Mitzy?

25:32.880 --> 25:33.960
She's my best friend.

25:33.960 --> 25:35.120
She's a dolphin.

25:35.120 --> 25:37.000
I can't wait for you
to meet her, grandma.

25:37.000 --> 25:37.880
A dolphin?

25:37.880 --> 25:39.000
How interesting.

25:39.000 --> 25:41.080
The ocean's pork.

25:41.080 --> 25:42.760
I once had dolphin
in St. Vincent.

25:42.760 --> 25:44.440
It was delicious.

25:44.440 --> 25:46.920
Not fishy at all--

25:47.920 --> 25:49.440
You know, Annabel,

25:49.440 --> 25:51.720
you are gonna love
Mr. and Mrs. Williams' townhome

25:51.720 --> 25:52.720
in Manhattan.

25:52.720 --> 25:54.080
Best of the best of everything.

25:54.080 --> 25:56.040
Aren't you a lucky little girl?

25:56.040 --> 25:57.880
I don't understand.

25:57.880 --> 26:00.760
I'd like to speak
to your grandparents, privately.

26:00.760 --> 26:01.920
Gramps.

26:01.920 --> 26:03.760
Now, please.

26:03.760 --> 26:05.320
Okay.

26:09.680 --> 26:12.640
Jonah, we just want to get
to know

26:12.640 --> 26:13.760
our granddaughter.

26:13.760 --> 26:15.920
Fine, then get to know her here.

26:15.920 --> 26:17.480
And watch as you allow her
to waste her life

26:17.480 --> 26:19.200
in this place?

26:19.200 --> 26:20.360
Uh, waste her life.

26:20.360 --> 26:22.480
You mean, like your daughter did
with my son?

26:23.920 --> 26:26.040
Debrah was a grown woman.

26:26.040 --> 26:27.240
There was nothin' I could do
about that.

26:27.240 --> 26:29.640
And there's nothing
you can do about Annabel.

26:29.640 --> 26:31.680
David and Debrah's will
made sure of that.

26:33.520 --> 26:35.960
Mr. Williams' law firm
has filed a motion

26:35.960 --> 26:38.800
to review Annabel's custody

26:38.800 --> 26:41.800
and a local judge has agreed
to a hearing.

26:42.840 --> 26:44.840
You've been served,
Mr. Coleridge.

26:47.800 --> 26:50.680
There's also a check here
for a quite tidy sum.

26:51.680 --> 26:53.520
That is reimbursement
for Annabel's care

26:53.520 --> 26:55.640
over the years.

26:55.640 --> 26:57.280
It's more
than I felt appropriate,

26:57.280 --> 27:00.280
but Mr. Williams
is a very generous man.

27:00.280 --> 27:02.400
Anna will have the best schools

27:02.400 --> 27:05.160
and all the opportunities
we can provide her.

27:05.160 --> 27:07.800
You can come
and visit her anytime you like.

27:07.800 --> 27:10.640
We wouldn't think
of keeping you apart.

27:10.640 --> 27:13.000
You want to buy Annabel.

27:13.000 --> 27:13.960
No, we would nev--

27:13.960 --> 27:15.880
Just like you tried
to buy off David,

27:15.880 --> 27:18.280
because you didn't think he was
good enough for your daughter

27:18.280 --> 27:19.720
and Debrah hated you for it.

27:19.720 --> 27:21.840
My relationship with my daughter
is none of your business!

27:21.840 --> 27:23.840
You haven't changed at all,
have you?

27:25.280 --> 27:28.280
I suggest you be reasonable,
Mr. Coleridge.

27:28.280 --> 27:30.440
Oh, do you suggest that,
Mr. Carbunkle?

27:30.440 --> 27:33.240
Well, I suggest
that you take your check

27:33.240 --> 27:35.440
and you roll it
into a very tight ball

27:35.440 --> 27:36.880
and you shove it directly
into his--

27:50.320 --> 27:52.720
A guy like that,
never listens to reason.

27:54.160 --> 27:56.120
What are our chances
at the hearin'?

27:56.120 --> 27:57.440
About even.

27:57.440 --> 27:59.400
Tell you what though,
money can goes a long way,

27:59.400 --> 28:01.160
if you would just
let me take a pile of it--

28:01.160 --> 28:04.000
No.

28:04.000 --> 28:06.120
I told you
I want this all above board.

28:07.800 --> 28:10.800
This is about what's best
for Annabel.

28:10.800 --> 28:12.720
Nothing else.

28:13.200 --> 28:21.520
[♪♪♪]

28:21.520 --> 28:23.040
Excuse me.

28:23.040 --> 28:24.880
I'm looking for a Mrs. Rolle.

28:24.880 --> 28:26.040
Oh, of course.

28:26.040 --> 28:27.800
-Over there.
-Thank you.

28:30.800 --> 28:33.800
Mrs. Rolle, I understand you are
the case worker

28:33.800 --> 28:36.080
for Anna Coleridge.

28:36.080 --> 28:38.040
And you are?

28:42.040 --> 28:43.920
A barrister?

28:43.920 --> 28:45.800
I represent her grandparents.

28:45.800 --> 28:47.840
I was wondering
if I could get a copy

28:47.840 --> 28:50.640
of your report
on Anna's situation?

28:50.640 --> 28:53.240
Oh, I haven't completed
that report.

28:53.240 --> 28:55.520
I haven't interviewed Anna yet.

28:55.520 --> 28:57.920
Oh, I see.

28:57.920 --> 28:59.920
Are there any
preliminary observations

28:59.920 --> 29:01.040
you could share?

29:01.040 --> 29:02.840
[Carbunkle]
Unofficially, of course.

29:02.840 --> 29:03.800
Between you and me,

29:03.800 --> 29:05.800
her grandparents
are very concerned

29:05.800 --> 29:07.520
about Anna's well-being.

29:07.520 --> 29:08.680
I can imagine.

29:08.680 --> 29:10.800
I've had the pleasure
of meeting Mr. Coleridge.

29:10.800 --> 29:11.800
[chuckling]

29:11.800 --> 29:12.800
[Carbunkle]
As have I.

29:12.800 --> 29:14.520
And frankly, I'm worried
he isn't thinkin'

29:14.520 --> 29:15.520
about what's best for Anna.

29:15.520 --> 29:17.400
Oh, those kind never do.

29:17.400 --> 29:19.640
Beach bums
on permanent holiday.

29:19.640 --> 29:20.840
Drinkin' all the time.

29:20.840 --> 29:21.840
Can't be relied on

29:21.840 --> 29:23.400
to put a child's needs ahead
of their own.

29:23.400 --> 29:25.880
I've met a lot of men like that.

29:25.880 --> 29:28.520
I was married
to a man like that.

29:28.520 --> 29:29.840
[chuckling]

29:29.840 --> 29:32.680
Well, it'll be completed
in a few days.

29:33.880 --> 29:35.960
That'll be just fine,
Mrs. Rolle.

29:35.960 --> 29:38.520
And thank you very much.

29:47.280 --> 29:48.840
[Carbunkle]
Mmhmm.

29:48.840 --> 29:49.680
Yes, sir, but--

29:49.680 --> 29:51.280
[Carbunkle sighs]

29:51.280 --> 29:54.280
I s-- yes, but if--

29:54.280 --> 29:55.560
Yes, sir.

29:55.560 --> 29:57.320
I agree with you, sir.

29:57.320 --> 29:58.280
Yes.

29:58.280 --> 30:01.000
Let me just say this though,
I--

30:01.000 --> 30:01.920
Yes, sir.

30:01.920 --> 30:03.880
The meeting
did not go as planned,

30:03.880 --> 30:04.880
but there were human variables.

30:04.880 --> 30:06.280
And I tell you what,

30:06.280 --> 30:08.400
the one constant that you can
have with human variables,

30:08.400 --> 30:11.000
especially officials, is money

30:11.000 --> 30:13.720
and that-- no, no, sir,
I don't mean to bribe

30:13.720 --> 30:16.400
necessarily, but perhaps
to grease

30:16.400 --> 30:18.280
a few palms, sir.

30:18.280 --> 30:19.320
[chuckling]

30:19.320 --> 30:20.160
Sir?

30:20.160 --> 30:21.720
Mr. Williams?

30:21.720 --> 30:22.760
Unbelievable!

30:22.760 --> 30:24.000
He did it again.

30:24.000 --> 30:26.440
Hey, are you tryin'
to steal my wallet?

30:26.440 --> 30:27.920
I just found this and--

30:27.920 --> 30:29.600
-I was gonna give it back.
-Yeah, right.

30:29.600 --> 30:31.840
That's the oldest con
in the book.

30:31.840 --> 30:40.360
[♪♪♪]

30:40.360 --> 30:42.880
[taking deep breaths]

30:42.880 --> 30:54.600
[♪♪♪]

30:54.600 --> 30:56.040
You know, I'm a lawyer.

30:56.040 --> 30:57.320
A lawyer?

30:57.320 --> 30:58.520
I thought you were a pirate.

30:58.520 --> 31:00.800
I have a suit.

31:00.800 --> 31:03.600
Look, I can sue your parents
for pain and suffering

31:03.600 --> 31:05.480
makin' me walk all this way.

31:13.240 --> 31:15.920
[grunting]

31:15.920 --> 31:16.680
Stop it!

31:16.680 --> 31:17.520
Whoa!

31:17.520 --> 31:20.320
[screaming]

31:20.320 --> 31:21.760
[chuckling]

31:21.760 --> 31:24.240
Wait a-- come on!

31:24.240 --> 31:25.240
Oh!

31:25.240 --> 31:27.080
[grunting]

31:27.080 --> 31:28.640
That's why people eat dolphin.

31:28.640 --> 31:30.480
[grunting]

31:30.480 --> 31:38.080
[♪♪♪]

31:38.080 --> 31:38.720
Wooh!

31:38.720 --> 31:39.720
[taking deep breaths]

31:39.720 --> 31:41.200
Did you do that on purpose?

31:45.360 --> 31:46.800
[chuckles]

31:46.800 --> 31:49.800
Well, thanks, partner.

31:49.800 --> 31:50.920
Hey!

31:50.920 --> 31:52.360
Not that!

31:52.360 --> 31:53.960
[Mateo]
My dad gave me that.

31:58.280 --> 31:59.840
[grunts]

32:04.960 --> 32:07.560
[chuckling]

32:07.560 --> 32:10.560
Mitzy.

32:10.560 --> 32:12.840
Where did you get this?

32:12.840 --> 32:14.360
She got it from me.

32:16.520 --> 32:19.040
Mitzy would never take something
that didn't belong to her.

32:19.040 --> 32:20.840
Yes, she would.

32:20.840 --> 32:22.880
You need to teach that fish
stealing is wrong.

32:22.880 --> 32:24.000
Mammal.

32:24.000 --> 32:25.440
What?

32:25.440 --> 32:27.680
Dolphins aren't fish,
they're mammals.

32:27.680 --> 32:29.320
And how do I know this is yours?

32:29.320 --> 32:32.120
It has my name written in it.

32:32.120 --> 32:34.440
Is your name
"one size fits all"?

32:34.440 --> 32:35.200
[chuckles]

32:35.200 --> 32:36.320
Mateo.

32:36.320 --> 32:37.400
Mateo Rolle.

32:37.400 --> 32:38.880
[chuckles]

32:38.880 --> 32:40.440
I guess this is yours then.

32:40.440 --> 32:58.880
[♪♪♪]

32:58.880 --> 33:01.880
[chuckling]

33:01.880 --> 33:12.600
[♪♪♪]

33:12.600 --> 33:13.720
Wait.

33:13.720 --> 33:16.040
You have to have permission
to come aboard.

33:17.600 --> 33:20.120
Permission to come aboard,
Captain?

33:20.120 --> 33:21.080
[chuckling]

33:21.080 --> 33:22.920
Come ahead.

33:25.600 --> 33:26.920
I remember you.

33:26.920 --> 33:29.080
You have nerve calling Mitzy
"a thief".

33:29.080 --> 33:30.360
I remember you, too.

33:30.360 --> 33:32.080
My name is Annabel.

33:36.920 --> 33:38.800
Is she yours?

33:38.800 --> 33:41.360
Mitzy belongs to Mitzy,

33:41.360 --> 33:44.040
but she lives here
at the center.

33:44.040 --> 33:45.480
What even is this place?

33:45.480 --> 33:48.400
It's a wildlife research and
conservation center.

33:48.400 --> 33:49.560
My parents founded it.

33:49.560 --> 33:51.080
They were marine biologists.

33:51.080 --> 33:52.400
Cool.

33:52.400 --> 33:54.480
You going
to the fish fry tonight?

33:54.480 --> 33:55.800
Uh, I don't usually.

33:55.800 --> 33:57.400
Why not?

33:57.400 --> 33:59.400
Everyone goes.

33:59.400 --> 34:01.280
It's just I have
a lot of work to do.

34:01.280 --> 34:04.280
Even a marine biologist
takes a break once in a while.

34:07.360 --> 34:08.480
Maybe.

34:08.480 --> 34:10.240
Great.

34:10.240 --> 34:11.960
I'll see you there.

34:11.960 --> 34:22.960
[♪♪♪]

34:33.120 --> 34:34.960
Oh, ahoy there.

34:34.960 --> 34:36.160
Well, don't you look nice?

34:36.160 --> 34:37.320
I don't look nice.

34:37.320 --> 34:38.560
I look regular.

34:38.560 --> 34:40.840
Which for you is nice.

34:40.840 --> 34:42.960
-Where you off to?
-Uh, me?

34:42.960 --> 34:44.280
Nowhere.

34:44.280 --> 34:45.880
I mean I was thinking
about going to the fish fry.

34:45.880 --> 34:46.880
You know, by the marina.

34:46.880 --> 34:48.920
Yes,
I know where the fish fry is.

34:48.920 --> 34:49.840
Who are you going with?

34:49.840 --> 34:51.520
Nobody!

34:51.520 --> 34:52.440
Hi, Mr. Coleridge.

34:52.440 --> 34:53.560
Hi, Anna.

34:53.560 --> 34:55.160
-Hi, Mr. Coleridge.
-Hi, Mr. Coleridge.

34:55.160 --> 34:56.160
Are you ready to go?

34:56.160 --> 34:57.400
Hi.

34:57.400 --> 34:58.320
[chuckles]

34:58.320 --> 34:59.280
Nobody?

34:59.280 --> 35:01.760
Nobody but my girlfriends.

35:01.760 --> 35:04.760
You know, they're girls
like Megan, and Kylie,

35:04.760 --> 35:07.160
and other girls.

35:07.160 --> 35:08.000
[kissing]

35:08.000 --> 35:08.640
Bye.

35:08.640 --> 35:10.200
See you later.

35:10.200 --> 35:12.280
Oh, excuse me?

35:12.280 --> 35:15.320
Are you acting strangely
or is this just 14 happening?

35:15.320 --> 35:16.840
How can I tell?

35:16.840 --> 35:18.120
Right.

35:18.120 --> 35:20.840
Come home early
and no walking alone after dark.

35:20.840 --> 35:21.760
Alright, standard rules.

35:21.760 --> 35:23.560
Bye, see you later!

35:23.560 --> 35:25.760
I mean, see you early!

35:28.880 --> 35:31.920
David, Debrah,

35:33.240 --> 35:36.080
your little girl is growing up.

35:37.080 --> 35:40.080
God help me.

35:40.080 --> 35:41.800
[sighing]

