36:54.240 --> 36:58.240
And then after my parents died,
my gramps,

36:58.240 --> 37:01.040
he came from England
to take care of me.

37:01.040 --> 37:04.040
Now, I sort of take care of him.

37:04.040 --> 37:05.760
You're lucky.

37:05.760 --> 37:07.720
How is any of that lucky?

37:07.720 --> 37:09.720
Your parents wanted
to be with you.

37:09.720 --> 37:11.160
[Mateo]
My pops took off
for the last time

37:11.160 --> 37:13.280
when I was about 9.

37:13.280 --> 37:15.280
And he only left me this hat.

37:17.440 --> 37:19.960
Do you wanna go and swim with me
and Mitzy tomorrow?

37:19.960 --> 37:21.440
Yeah.

37:21.440 --> 37:22.880
Oh.

37:22.880 --> 37:25.600
But me and moms
always hangs out on Sunday.

37:25.600 --> 37:26.840
She can come, too.

37:26.840 --> 37:29.280
It will be lots of fun.

37:29.280 --> 37:30.160
Great.

37:30.160 --> 37:31.760
I'll ask.

37:37.440 --> 37:38.720
[Mateo]
Hey, moms.

37:38.720 --> 37:39.920
[Desaray]
Hi.

37:39.920 --> 37:41.080
How was the fish fry?

37:41.080 --> 37:43.040
It was good.

37:43.040 --> 37:45.600
[Desaray]
Huh, who was there?

37:45.600 --> 37:48.440
Um, a really super cool girl.

37:50.200 --> 37:53.200
[Desaray]
Ooh, hoo, hoo,
you met a really cool girl.

37:53.200 --> 37:55.480
Nice.

37:55.480 --> 37:58.040
Use a fork.

37:58.040 --> 38:01.040
Hmm.

38:01.040 --> 38:02.360
Do you have work tomorrow?

38:02.360 --> 38:03.400
Mm-mm.

38:03.400 --> 38:04.400
I have to finish a report

38:04.400 --> 38:05.480
on this girl
and her grandfather,

38:05.480 --> 38:06.760
but I'll get that done early.

38:06.760 --> 38:09.480
So what do you wanna do
tomorrow?

38:09.480 --> 38:10.640
Movie?

38:10.640 --> 38:12.000
[Desaray]
Pizza?

38:12.000 --> 38:15.040
Actually,
I've got a better idea.

38:15.800 --> 38:23.840
[♪♪♪]

38:23.840 --> 38:25.080
[chuckling]

38:25.080 --> 38:25.800
[sighing]

38:25.800 --> 38:27.040
It's nice to be out.

38:27.040 --> 38:29.400
Oh, a girl over there.

38:30.400 --> 38:32.760
[Desaray chuckling]

38:32.760 --> 38:34.360
We here!

38:34.360 --> 38:35.560
[Annabel]
You made it!

38:35.560 --> 38:37.680
[Annabel chuckling]

38:37.680 --> 38:38.680
You must be Mateo.

38:38.680 --> 38:40.520
Welcome
to the conservation center.

38:40.520 --> 38:41.640
Thanks.

38:41.640 --> 38:42.800
Hey, you wanna swim
with dolphins later?

38:42.800 --> 38:43.400
Yeah, thanks!

38:43.400 --> 38:44.200
[chuckles]

38:44.200 --> 38:46.960
This is my moms.

38:46.960 --> 38:48.960
You?

38:48.960 --> 38:50.440
Mr. Coleridge!

38:50.440 --> 38:53.240
I guess that my son
has met your granddaughter.

38:54.240 --> 38:55.840
You guys know each other?

38:55.840 --> 38:57.440
Your mom is our social worker.

38:57.440 --> 38:59.640
She judges us.

38:59.640 --> 39:02.400
If this is too awkward,
I can leave.

39:02.400 --> 39:03.840
Oh, no, no, no!

39:03.840 --> 39:04.960
Don't leave.

39:04.960 --> 39:06.800
You said you wanted
to talk to me, remember?

39:06.800 --> 39:07.640
We can talk and swim.

39:07.640 --> 39:10.240
Right, gramps?

39:10.240 --> 39:13.280
Well, if your grandfather
doesn't mind.

39:14.680 --> 39:15.400
Uh, yes.

39:15.400 --> 39:16.560
No, no, no.

39:16.560 --> 39:18.840
Um, you and Mateo are--

39:18.840 --> 39:21.680
you're very welcome,
Mrs. Rolle.

39:21.680 --> 39:22.600
Yay, great!

39:22.600 --> 39:25.600
[chuckling]

39:28.400 --> 39:30.440
So should we um

39:30.440 --> 39:33.440
Absolutely.

39:33.440 --> 39:35.400
[chuckling]

39:37.040 --> 39:57.040
[♪♪♪]

39:57.040 --> 40:17.080
[♪♪♪]

40:17.080 --> 40:31.760
[♪♪♪]

40:31.760 --> 40:33.360
I haven't seen Mateo
have this much fun

40:33.360 --> 40:35.320
in a long time.

40:37.800 --> 40:40.040
Would you like
to take a look around?

40:40.040 --> 40:41.800
I would.

40:41.800 --> 40:43.200
Thank you.

40:43.200 --> 40:45.800
Annabel, I'm gonna
show Mrs. Rolle around.

40:46.800 --> 40:47.920
Okay.

40:47.920 --> 40:49.800
Bye!

40:49.800 --> 40:59.120
[♪♪♪]

40:59.120 --> 40:59.920
You see him?

40:59.920 --> 41:00.920
[chuckling]

41:00.920 --> 41:02.360
We don't mess with this one.

41:05.120 --> 41:08.120
You wanna come on here?

41:08.120 --> 41:10.080
There you go.

41:10.080 --> 41:13.080
She's one of our oldest birds.

41:13.080 --> 41:15.400
Okay, little one.

41:15.400 --> 41:17.200
Yeah.

41:17.200 --> 41:18.400
[Jonah]
There you go.

41:18.400 --> 41:36.440
[♪♪♪]

41:36.440 --> 41:38.000
Can I get you a drink?

41:38.000 --> 41:40.720
I only have is soda
and water I'm afraid.

41:40.720 --> 41:41.720
I made some tea this morning.

41:41.720 --> 41:44.680
You could have Anna's
if you like.

41:44.680 --> 41:46.800
I'd love some tea.

41:50.160 --> 41:52.040
Thank you.

41:54.840 --> 41:57.840
[sighing]

41:58.880 --> 42:00.280
This place is beautiful.

42:00.280 --> 42:02.560
[chuckles]

42:02.560 --> 42:04.720
It was my son David's dream.

42:04.720 --> 42:07.720
And Debrah's, too.

42:07.720 --> 42:09.720
They wanted Anna
to be raised here.

42:09.720 --> 42:12.160
So how did you come
to the island?

42:12.160 --> 42:14.640
Still finishing your report,
Mrs. Rolle?

42:14.640 --> 42:15.600
I'm sorry.

42:15.600 --> 42:16.720
We got off on the wrong foot.

42:16.720 --> 42:17.640
[chuckles]

42:17.640 --> 42:20.040
Call me "Desaray".

42:20.040 --> 42:22.320
Jonah.

42:22.320 --> 42:24.600
And the fault was mine.

42:24.600 --> 42:26.640
I get over-protective
when it comes to Anna.

42:30.640 --> 42:33.640
So what happened to her parents?

42:35.040 --> 42:37.600
They were killed
in a diving accident

42:37.600 --> 42:40.080
10 years ago.

42:40.080 --> 42:41.680
[Jonah]
Mitzy was a juvenile then.

42:41.680 --> 42:44.680
She got snared
in a fisherman's net.

42:44.680 --> 42:46.880
David freed her,
but he got snared himself

42:46.880 --> 42:49.880
and Debrah tried to help.

42:49.880 --> 42:52.880
Oh, it's just one
of those things that happens.

42:54.480 --> 42:56.760
Anna was 5 years old.

42:56.760 --> 42:59.760
I'm so sorry.

42:59.760 --> 43:02.320
I was teaching history
at Cambridge.

43:03.320 --> 43:05.680
When I came back for funeral,

43:05.680 --> 43:07.480
I discovered that they'd
appointed me guardian

43:07.480 --> 43:09.360
of Anna

43:09.360 --> 43:11.760
and left me their boat.

43:13.680 --> 43:16.680
So Anna and I have
been shipmates ever since.

43:18.080 --> 43:20.480
Why didn't you take her back
to England?

43:21.800 --> 43:22.920
You ever been there?

43:22.920 --> 43:23.920
No.

43:23.920 --> 43:25.240
[chuckles]

43:25.240 --> 43:28.080
Well, it's just
like everywhere else I suppose.

43:28.080 --> 43:31.080
People fighting, and hating,
and grabbing from each other,

43:31.080 --> 43:33.520
because they're scared.

43:33.520 --> 43:36.520
Scared of being left behind,
scared of not having enough,

43:36.520 --> 43:38.440
scared of just being scared
all the time.

43:43.040 --> 43:45.240
And I realized

43:45.240 --> 43:48.120
what a special place
this island is

43:48.120 --> 43:51.120
and how remarkable
the people in it are.

43:53.640 --> 43:56.560
Anna's all I have left
of my boy.

43:56.560 --> 43:59.560
I wanted to teach her how
to be happy.

43:59.560 --> 44:01.520
Instead, she taught me.

44:04.680 --> 44:06.360
You gonna put all that
in your report?

44:06.360 --> 44:08.360
Uh, definitely.

44:08.360 --> 44:21.120
[♪♪♪]

44:21.120 --> 44:22.080
[indistinct speech]

44:22.080 --> 44:24.000
[laughing]

44:24.000 --> 44:33.600
[♪♪♪]

44:33.600 --> 44:36.440
Oh, thank you, Mitzy.

44:36.440 --> 44:37.720
[chuckling]

44:37.720 --> 44:39.800
Mitzy is very tidy.

44:39.800 --> 44:40.480
Yes.

44:40.480 --> 44:41.600
[chuckling]

44:41.600 --> 44:43.880
I'm constantly going
to the recycling center

44:43.880 --> 44:46.200
with whole bags of the refuse

44:46.200 --> 44:48.640
that she brings up out
of the water.

44:48.640 --> 44:50.320
Oh.

44:50.320 --> 44:52.000
Oh, that explains it.

44:52.000 --> 44:54.000
[chuckling]

44:54.000 --> 44:55.120
Explains what?

44:55.120 --> 44:56.280
Nothing.

44:56.280 --> 44:58.040
Nothing.

45:02.640 --> 45:04.440
[sighing]

45:04.440 --> 45:05.480
Oh, no, no, Mateo.

45:05.480 --> 45:06.520
You keep that, it's chilly.

45:06.520 --> 45:08.640
Oh, thanks, Mr. Coleridge.

45:08.640 --> 45:10.640
Thank you, Jonah,
for a wonderful day,

45:10.640 --> 45:11.880
You are very welcome, Desaray.

45:11.880 --> 45:14.800
You and Mateo can come
to the boat anytime you like.

45:14.800 --> 45:16.480
Or maybe next time
we'll go out?

45:16.480 --> 45:19.440
Oh, I'd like that.

45:19.440 --> 45:20.920
See you later, Anna.

45:20.920 --> 45:23.920
Bye.

45:23.920 --> 45:26.200
-Alright, come on.
-Bye.

45:28.640 --> 45:30.360
[chuckling]

45:30.360 --> 45:32.520
-Did you have a good time?
-Of course.

45:32.520 --> 45:33.800
You?

45:33.800 --> 45:35.800
Yes.

45:35.800 --> 45:37.480
I think I did.

45:37.480 --> 45:38.360
[chuckles]

45:38.360 --> 45:40.200
I'm gonna go change.

45:43.800 --> 45:45.400
[chuckles]

46:06.840 --> 46:09.480
[coughing]

46:10.520 --> 46:11.800
Sheryl, are you all right?

46:11.800 --> 46:14.240
I'm fine.

46:15.240 --> 46:17.720
The doctor said
the last scan was clear.

46:17.720 --> 46:20.400
It was and I'm fine.

46:20.400 --> 46:22.560
It's just a cough.

46:22.560 --> 46:23.840
You fret too much.

46:23.840 --> 46:26.840
[chuckles]

46:26.840 --> 46:29.400
Sam--

46:29.400 --> 46:32.400
I know the last few months
have been hard on you.

46:33.840 --> 46:36.280
Is that why we're doing this?

46:36.280 --> 46:37.320
I'm doing this

46:37.320 --> 46:39.920
because it's the right thing
for Annabel.

46:39.920 --> 46:42.400
She seems so happy here.

46:43.560 --> 46:46.560
But what kind of life
will she have?

46:46.560 --> 46:49.560
She's a smart talented girl.

46:49.560 --> 46:52.440
She deserves more than this.

46:53.440 --> 46:55.880
She deserves her chance
at the world.

46:55.880 --> 46:58.320
The chance Debrah never had.

46:59.280 --> 47:02.280
She's so like our Deb,
isn't she?

47:03.360 --> 47:05.320
She is.

47:07.720 --> 47:10.200
When she's older,

47:10.200 --> 47:12.040
she'll appreciate
what we're doing for her.

47:15.480 --> 47:17.600
I hope so.

47:28.080 --> 47:30.680
Oh, Mr. Williams,
what can I do for you?

47:34.920 --> 47:37.920
My wife is becoming confused.

47:37.920 --> 47:40.880
We need to expedite matters.

47:40.880 --> 47:43.880
I will not lose Anna
the way I did Deb.

47:46.960 --> 47:49.960
Is there anything more you
could be doing?

47:49.960 --> 47:52.960
Not uh, within the parameters
you established.

47:57.320 --> 48:00.320
Do what you have to do,

48:00.320 --> 48:02.760
but you get it done.

48:02.760 --> 48:19.360
[♪♪♪]

48:19.360 --> 48:20.840
Ah, Mr. Coleridge.

48:20.840 --> 48:23.840
Lovely day for boat fiddling.

48:23.840 --> 48:25.440
[sighs]

48:25.440 --> 48:26.440
You.

48:26.440 --> 48:28.920
[grunting]

48:28.920 --> 48:31.800
You know, I keep telling people

48:31.800 --> 48:34.440
that this is a private dock.

48:34.440 --> 48:36.440
You think I should
put up a sign?

48:36.440 --> 48:38.800
You know, I wouldn't bother.

48:38.800 --> 48:41.800
[taking deep breaths]

48:49.640 --> 48:52.640
My fishing license.

48:52.640 --> 48:54.680
It's been revoked.

48:54.680 --> 48:57.120
Yeah, it seems there were
some irregularities

48:57.120 --> 48:58.760
when you renewed it.

48:58.760 --> 49:00.400
And commercial fishing
without a license

49:00.400 --> 49:02.400
carries some hefty fines.

49:02.400 --> 49:04.160
Those will need
to be paid promptly

49:04.160 --> 49:06.880
or your vessel here

49:06.880 --> 49:08.600
could be impounded.

49:08.600 --> 49:11.600
Fortunately, Mr. Williams' offer

49:11.600 --> 49:14.120
is still on the table.

49:14.120 --> 49:17.160
Sam Williams is
not buying my granddaughter.

49:18.000 --> 49:19.160
Oh, of course he is.

49:19.160 --> 49:21.200
That's how the world works.

49:21.200 --> 49:22.600
Your world.

49:22.600 --> 49:24.440
Not mine.

49:24.440 --> 49:27.440
You know,
you sit on this grubby boat,

49:28.400 --> 49:30.720
on this stinking dock,

49:30.720 --> 49:33.760
surrounded by losers and bums,

49:34.920 --> 49:37.400
and you wanna fight me?

49:37.400 --> 49:39.800
Look, make this easy
and you'll still be in her life.

49:41.040 --> 49:42.880
But you make it hard,

49:42.880 --> 49:45.880
I will shut down this
Dr. Dolittle fantasy of yours.

49:47.000 --> 49:50.000
And I guarantee you will never
see your granddaughter again.

49:51.600 --> 49:53.480
Good day, Mr. Coleridge.

49:58.920 --> 50:00.000
[sighing]

50:02.080 --> 50:03.760
Mrs. Rolle.

50:09.920 --> 50:12.800
I came by to return the towel
you loaned Mateo

50:12.800 --> 50:15.800
and to tell you

50:15.800 --> 50:18.480
that your review
has been officially closed.

50:24.800 --> 50:27.360
What's wrong?

50:27.360 --> 50:30.400
Uh, I just don't understand
how people can be so terrible.

50:32.080 --> 50:34.040
Who's terrible?

50:35.800 --> 50:37.800
It's a long story.

50:37.800 --> 50:40.800
[Desaray]
I'm a good listener.

50:42.120 --> 50:44.480
How about dinner?

50:48.960 --> 50:49.960
uh, um.

50:49.960 --> 50:50.560
[clears throat]

50:50.560 --> 50:51.840
Anna!

50:51.840 --> 50:52.840
[chuckles]

50:52.840 --> 50:54.000
What?

50:54.000 --> 50:55.000
What is it?

50:55.000 --> 50:56.960
-Oh, hi, Ms. Rolle.
-Hi.

50:56.960 --> 50:59.840
Um, would you be alright
fixing your own dinner tonight?

50:59.840 --> 51:01.720
Sure, why?

51:01.720 --> 51:03.080
Why, yes, why.

51:03.080 --> 51:05.720
Well, um, uh, Desaray and I,
we thought we might--

51:05.720 --> 51:06.800
Well, you know,
we were thinking--

51:06.800 --> 51:07.800
Really?

51:07.800 --> 51:08.960
No, no!

51:08.960 --> 51:11.120
-I mean, not if you need me to-- -No, no, no, no, no, no!

51:11.120 --> 51:12.560
This is great.

51:12.560 --> 51:13.720
Yaw-haw are great.

51:13.720 --> 51:15.720
Um, Ms. Rolle,
just give us a second.

51:15.720 --> 51:16.960
Why?

51:16.960 --> 51:17.960
What's happening?

51:17.960 --> 51:19.200
You are not wearing those.

51:19.200 --> 51:20.000
Oh, I think I am.

51:20.000 --> 51:21.520
-Look, see?
-No, no.

51:21.520 --> 51:23.600
You need to put on
your nice pants.

51:23.600 --> 51:25.680
Well, these shorts are nice.

51:25.680 --> 51:27.440
Those shorts
are the opposite of nice.

51:27.440 --> 51:30.440
Nice runs and hides
from those shorts.

51:30.440 --> 51:32.200
Alright, I'll change.

51:32.200 --> 51:34.160
And your shirt.

51:34.160 --> 51:34.920
Shirt.

51:34.920 --> 51:36.000
Fine, fine.

51:36.000 --> 51:37.120
And put on your nice jacket!

51:37.120 --> 51:39.160
[Jonah]
Yes, alright!

51:39.160 --> 51:40.280
He'll be right out.

51:40.280 --> 51:42.000
You're gonna love the jacket.

51:42.000 --> 52:01.000
[♪♪♪]

52:02.480 --> 52:05.200
That was your mother

52:05.200 --> 52:08.200
when she was about your age.

52:08.200 --> 52:10.760
She's beautiful.

52:10.760 --> 52:13.600
You look very much like her.

52:14.600 --> 52:17.600
So why didn't grandfather
and her not get along?

52:20.160 --> 52:22.560
From the moment Debrah was born,

52:22.560 --> 52:25.320
She was everything
to your grandfather.

52:25.320 --> 52:27.800
The two were inseparable.

52:28.800 --> 52:30.800
[Sheryl]
So much love.

52:32.240 --> 52:35.240
Sam thought Debrah had
a great career ahead of her.

52:36.640 --> 52:39.640
But when your mother
met your father,

52:39.640 --> 52:42.200
she left her position at UNICO

52:42.200 --> 52:45.200
and uh, came down here
to work with him.

52:48.280 --> 52:51.280
Sam thought it was
a waste of her talent.

52:52.880 --> 52:55.920
So he offered your father money
to fire Debrah.

52:57.400 --> 53:00.200
[Sheryl]
A lot of money.

53:00.200 --> 53:03.200
Would have funded his research
for years.

53:05.680 --> 53:08.680
David didn't even
think about it.

53:08.680 --> 53:11.680
Wand when Deb found out,
oh, the fight they had.

53:12.960 --> 53:15.960
I've never seen either of them
so angry.

53:17.400 --> 53:19.120
[Sheryl]
I always thought that if Debrah
had lived longer

53:19.120 --> 53:22.120
they would have
found their way back together.

53:22.120 --> 53:24.080
But um

53:27.920 --> 53:30.920
Anna,
your grandfather is a good man.

53:32.520 --> 53:35.160
He loves you very much.

53:35.160 --> 53:37.640
Then why do this?

53:39.280 --> 53:42.280
I think he's afraid
of being alone.

53:43.880 --> 53:45.840
I don't understand.

53:48.760 --> 53:50.000
Good.

53:50.000 --> 53:53.000
You are far too young
to understand that.

53:55.280 --> 53:57.440
I came here
to give you something.

54:02.360 --> 54:05.360
This was your mother's.

54:05.360 --> 54:07.880
They returned it to me
after the accident.

54:12.160 --> 54:14.360
It's beautiful.

54:14.360 --> 54:16.360
My mother gave it to me

54:18.040 --> 54:19.920
and I gave it to Debrah.

54:22.320 --> 54:24.160
I think she'd want you
to have it.

54:24.160 --> 54:26.040
I love you, grandma.

54:29.040 --> 54:30.800
I love you, too.

54:30.800 --> 54:33.800
Thank you, my dear, dear Anna.

54:34.920 --> 54:37.360
I'm so grateful
I got to hear that.

54:38.480 --> 54:40.920
And don't worry.

54:40.920 --> 54:43.920
Life has a way of working out

54:43.920 --> 54:46.240
just the way it's supposed to.

54:54.520 --> 54:57.520
So he just
flat out threatened you?

54:57.520 --> 54:58.960
The thing is Desaray,

54:58.960 --> 55:01.200
I'm not sure
he can't do what he says.

55:01.200 --> 55:03.360
Well, he'd have to have some
pretty overwhelming evidence

55:03.360 --> 55:05.920
to get custody of a minor
overturned.

55:06.920 --> 55:08.920
You and Annabel belong together.

55:08.920 --> 55:10.960
Everyone can see that.

55:10.960 --> 55:12.920
[chuckles]

55:21.400 --> 55:22.680
Uh, thanks.

55:22.680 --> 55:23.960
[chuckles]

55:23.960 --> 55:25.920
Huh.

55:27.280 --> 55:29.520
Still worried about Annabel,
huh?

55:29.520 --> 55:31.400
Yes.

55:31.400 --> 55:32.920
Sorry.

55:32.920 --> 55:34.800
And my license.

55:34.800 --> 55:36.240
You can file an appeal.

55:36.240 --> 55:38.800
I mean, you can
always file an extension.

55:38.800 --> 55:40.400
No one's gonna
take Annabel away from you

55:40.400 --> 55:42.440
because an off-islander dug up

55:42.440 --> 55:44.280
a misfiled fishing license.

55:44.280 --> 55:45.240
You think so?

55:45.240 --> 55:47.080
I'm sure of it.

55:48.240 --> 55:49.240
Nice, Desaray.

55:49.240 --> 55:52.000
I mean, really thanks.

55:52.000 --> 55:52.800
[sighs]

55:52.800 --> 55:55.400
Uh, you've been very good.

55:56.400 --> 55:59.280
I know how much you care
about Annabel.

55:59.280 --> 56:01.800
And I wanna help you
if I can.

56:01.800 --> 56:02.840
Uh, you have helped.

56:02.840 --> 56:05.440
Just by being a friend.

56:05.440 --> 56:07.960
I wanna be your friend.

56:07.960 --> 56:09.480
[chuckling]

56:09.480 --> 56:12.480
At the very least, I hope.

56:12.480 --> 56:32.480
[♪♪♪]

56:32.480 --> 56:52.720
[♪♪♪]

56:52.720 --> 56:55.720
[takes a deep breath]

57:03.360 --> 57:05.200
-Good night.
-Good night.

57:05.200 --> 57:06.360
[chuckles]

57:06.360 --> 57:08.200
Can I see you tomorrow?

57:08.200 --> 57:09.600
Absolutely.

57:14.960 --> 57:16.920
-Good night.
-Good night.

57:16.920 --> 57:26.920
[♪♪♪]

57:26.920 --> 57:28.800
[chuckling]

57:28.800 --> 57:30.520
Desaray!

57:30.520 --> 57:31.800
[Desaray]
Mr. Carbunkle.

57:31.800 --> 57:34.560
I was just at your office,
they said you left early.

57:34.560 --> 57:36.640
Report all done?

57:36.640 --> 57:38.120
It is.

57:38.120 --> 57:39.520
I'm afraid you won't like it.

57:39.520 --> 57:42.240
Oh, that's disappointing.

57:42.240 --> 57:43.480
My report says

57:43.480 --> 57:45.800
that Mr. Coleridge is
an excellent guardian

57:45.800 --> 57:47.800
and that Anna couldn't be
in a more loving, supportive,

57:47.800 --> 57:49.400
and stable home.

57:49.400 --> 57:51.080
Really?

57:51.080 --> 57:53.640
Huh.

57:53.640 --> 57:55.360
You know, is there any way
that you would

57:55.360 --> 57:58.200
consider reevaluating
those conclusions?

58:00.200 --> 58:01.960
I understand you're
a single mother

58:01.960 --> 58:03.600
on a government salary.

58:03.600 --> 58:05.960
Perhaps a consulting fee?

58:05.960 --> 58:08.960
You predecessor in this job
is quite enjoying

58:08.960 --> 58:11.840
his early retirement
from what I understand.

58:12.840 --> 58:15.440
You're responsible
for Mr. Lewis' retirement?

58:16.440 --> 58:19.120
His relationship to Coleridge
didn't seem helpful

58:19.120 --> 58:20.160
to our case.

58:20.160 --> 58:21.720
I thought it needed new eyes.

58:23.920 --> 58:26.320
You really don't wanna come down
on the wrong side of this,

58:26.320 --> 58:28.160
Mrs. Rolle.

58:28.160 --> 58:31.160
I have no intention of doing
so, Mr. Carbunkle.

58:31.160 --> 58:43.840
[♪♪♪]

58:51.360 --> 58:54.360
[humming]

58:59.000 --> 59:01.880
[chuckling]

59:01.880 --> 59:04.200
[sighing]

59:04.200 --> 59:05.200
Hey, moms.

59:05.200 --> 59:06.600
Hey, honey.

59:06.600 --> 59:07.760
Are you doin' homework?

59:07.760 --> 59:09.600
Yeah.

59:09.600 --> 59:12.040
But seems like you had
a good night.

59:13.880 --> 59:15.880
Good night.

59:17.440 --> 59:20.440
[humming]

59:20.440 --> 59:40.480
[♪♪♪]

59:41.680 --> 59:44.000
Hello?

59:44.000 --> 59:45.600
Hello?

59:45.600 --> 59:46.920
[Mr. Davies]
Mr. Carbunkle.

59:46.920 --> 59:48.360
Uh, Desaray isn't in yet.

59:48.360 --> 59:49.480
Oh.

59:49.480 --> 59:50.800
She asked me to meet her here.

59:50.800 --> 59:53.680
She said that she had some
important information for me.

59:53.680 --> 59:56.640
Something about a old complaint
about Mr. Coleridge.

59:56.640 --> 59:59.520
Uh, anything like that would be
on the computer files.

59:59.520 --> 1:00:00.800
I could get that for you.

1:00:00.800 --> 1:00:01.800
That would be fantatsic.

1:00:01.800 --> 1:00:02.960
I'm in a bit of a hurry.

1:00:02.960 --> 1:00:04.320
Court today and all.

1:00:04.320 --> 1:00:05.360
Of course. I'll be right back.

1:00:05.360 --> 1:00:06.960
Thank you.

1:00:06.960 --> 1:00:26.280
[♪♪♪]

1:00:26.280 --> 1:00:29.160
Stable nurturing home environment.

1:00:29.160 --> 1:00:31.560
Recommended custody stay
with Mr. Coleridge.

1:00:31.560 --> 1:00:51.600
[♪♪♪]

1:00:51.600 --> 1:00:58.680
[♪♪♪]

1:00:58.680 --> 1:01:01.680
I couldn't find the files
you were lookin' for uh--

1:01:01.680 --> 1:01:03.840
Mr. Carbunkle?

1:01:03.840 --> 1:01:05.560
Mr. Carbunkle?

1:01:05.560 --> 1:01:11.560
[♪♪♪]

1:01:11.560 --> 1:01:13.680
[Judge Swanson]
Well, good morning.

1:01:13.680 --> 1:01:14.760
Is everyone here?

1:01:14.760 --> 1:01:16.000
Your Worship,

1:01:16.000 --> 1:01:19.000
I am representing
Mr. and Mrs. Samuel Williams--

1:01:19.000 --> 1:01:21.920
[Carbunkle]
Who in are requesting
full legal custody

1:01:21.920 --> 1:01:24.760
Of their granddaughter Annabel

1:01:24.760 --> 1:01:27.760
and will present evidence
that my clients are capable,

1:01:27.760 --> 1:01:30.440
both physically and financially,

1:01:30.440 --> 1:01:32.480
to provide for the child
in a safer,

1:01:32.480 --> 1:01:33.920
more secure environment

1:01:33.920 --> 1:01:36.920
than she is presently
being provided here to for.

1:01:36.920 --> 1:01:38.160
I see.

1:01:38.160 --> 1:01:39.160
Sit down.

1:01:39.160 --> 1:01:40.160
[clears throat]

1:01:40.160 --> 1:01:43.040
Mrs. Rolle,
you are the case worker?

1:01:43.040 --> 1:01:44.720
-Yes, Your Worship.
-Okay.

1:01:44.720 --> 1:01:47.720
Could you give us a report
on Miss Coleridge's situation?

1:01:48.760 --> 1:01:51.200
Well, I have observed
in the past week

1:01:51.200 --> 1:01:52.720
a very strong bond

1:01:52.720 --> 1:01:55.520
between Mr. Coleridge
and Annabel.

1:01:55.520 --> 1:01:58.520
She appears to be a healthy,
normal, and loved young lady.

1:01:59.320 --> 1:02:00.440
I object!

1:02:00.440 --> 1:02:02.360
Your Worship, speculation.

1:02:02.360 --> 1:02:04.920
Mrs. Rolle is not
a trained medical physician

1:02:04.920 --> 1:02:07.840
and therefore cannot comment
on the health of the child.

1:02:08.800 --> 1:02:10.480
[Judge Swanson]
Mr. Carbunkle, sit down.

1:02:10.480 --> 1:02:12.240
This is not TV.

1:02:12.240 --> 1:02:15.200
Now, I've read all the materials

1:02:15.200 --> 1:02:16.480
submitted by both parties

1:02:16.480 --> 1:02:19.400
and I can't say I see

1:02:19.400 --> 1:02:22.360
any urgent cause to
change Miss Coleridge's living--

1:02:22.360 --> 1:02:25.360
Your Worship, I move to submit
further evidence.

1:02:25.360 --> 1:02:27.520
What other evidence?

1:02:27.520 --> 1:02:28.960
With the courts permission,

1:02:28.960 --> 1:02:31.960
I would like Mrs. Rolle
to read a few paragraphs--

1:02:31.960 --> 1:02:35.000
[Carbunkle]
From her initial report

1:02:35.000 --> 1:02:38.000
submitted before she started
an inappropriate

1:02:38.000 --> 1:02:41.000
intimate relationship with
Mr. Coleridge.

1:02:41.000 --> 1:02:42.480
What?

1:02:42.480 --> 1:02:45.480
Mr. Carbunkle,
that is a serious accusation.

1:02:45.480 --> 1:02:47.120
I have proof, Your Worship.

1:02:47.120 --> 1:02:54.880
[♪♪♪]

1:02:54.880 --> 1:02:57.080
Mrs. Rolle, you are aware

1:02:57.080 --> 1:02:58.840
that fraternization
with a client

1:02:58.840 --> 1:03:00.520
during an investigation

1:03:00.520 --> 1:03:03.320
is against
social services policies?

1:03:03.320 --> 1:03:05.840
Yes, I am, Your Worship.

1:03:05.840 --> 1:03:07.520
I have the report right here.

1:03:07.520 --> 1:03:08.960
Mrs. Rolle.

1:03:12.160 --> 1:03:14.040
I don't know where he got this.

1:03:14.040 --> 1:03:15.160
I--

1:03:15.160 --> 1:03:17.120
Are you saying
you didn't write it?

1:03:17.120 --> 1:03:19.000
No, I did.

1:03:21.040 --> 1:03:22.560
Well, then read it.

1:03:30.840 --> 1:03:32.760
"Annabel Coleridge is living

1:03:32.760 --> 1:03:35.760
with her grandfather
Jonah Coleridge

1:03:35.760 --> 1:03:38.760
on his fishing boat.

1:03:38.760 --> 1:03:41.720
It appears they share
the tiny bathroom

1:03:41.720 --> 1:03:44.000
And showering facilities.

1:03:44.000 --> 1:03:47.000
There was a distinct smell
of fish everywhere."

1:03:47.000 --> 1:03:48.480
It's a fishing boat!

1:03:48.480 --> 1:03:51.160
-How--
-Mr. Coleridge, let her finish.

1:03:53.280 --> 1:03:55.600
"From my brief encounter
with Mr. Coleridge,

1:03:55.600 --> 1:03:58.600
he seemed uncooperative,

1:03:58.600 --> 1:04:01.480
argumentative,
and unconcerned

1:04:02.640 --> 1:04:05.600
with the whereabouts
of his granddaughter.

1:04:06.600 --> 1:04:09.280
[Desaray]
Mr. Coleridge took no action
to address the issue

1:04:09.280 --> 1:04:12.280
but instead asked me to leave,

1:04:12.280 --> 1:04:14.760
denying me access to the subject

1:04:14.760 --> 1:04:16.640
of my evaluation.

1:04:18.680 --> 1:04:20.520
My preliminary recommendation
would be

1:04:20.520 --> 1:04:23.040
to place the girl in foster care

1:04:24.040 --> 1:04:26.520
for her own safety
and well-being

1:04:26.520 --> 1:04:29.080
until further investigation
takes place."

1:04:31.480 --> 1:04:33.640
This is not what it seems.

1:04:33.640 --> 1:04:36.520
I revaluated
and I revised

1:04:36.520 --> 1:04:37.640
the assessment.

1:04:37.640 --> 1:04:39.800
You mean you changed your report

1:04:39.800 --> 1:04:42.800
after you and Mr. Coleridge
started sleeping together.

1:04:42.800 --> 1:04:45.240
We're not sleeping together!

1:04:45.240 --> 1:04:46.760
Sit down, Mr. Coleridge.

1:04:46.760 --> 1:04:48.800
[Carbunkle]
Your Worship,

1:04:48.800 --> 1:04:51.240
in light of Ms. Rolle's
unprofessional behavior,

1:04:52.680 --> 1:04:55.680
I move that her submitted report

1:04:55.680 --> 1:04:58.400
be stricken in favor
of this more

1:04:58.400 --> 1:05:01.240
objective analysis
of Miss Coleridge's

1:05:01.240 --> 1:05:02.360
living conditions.

1:05:02.360 --> 1:05:03.240
You can't do that!

1:05:03.240 --> 1:05:04.960
[Judge Swanson]
Mrs. Rolle!

1:05:04.960 --> 1:05:07.960
I suggest you be very careful.

1:05:07.960 --> 1:05:09.800
Your conduct has been appalling

1:05:09.800 --> 1:05:11.400
and I will be bringing
this matter

1:05:11.400 --> 1:05:13.840
to the attention of Mr. Davies.

1:05:15.400 --> 1:05:16.400
Mr. Coleridge,

1:05:16.400 --> 1:05:17.920
do you have anything else
to say?

1:05:17.920 --> 1:05:25.120
[♪♪♪]

1:05:25.120 --> 1:05:27.880
My son and his wife,

1:05:28.880 --> 1:05:31.880
they wanted to raise Anna
on this island.

1:05:34.360 --> 1:05:37.360
The Williams' own daughter
wanted Anna

1:05:37.360 --> 1:05:40.360
to grow up with the values
that this place could teach her,

1:05:41.040 --> 1:05:44.040
surrounded by people
who love her.

1:05:45.240 --> 1:05:48.240
Anna is happy here.

1:05:49.760 --> 1:05:52.760
She belongs here.

1:05:52.760 --> 1:05:54.680
With me.

1:06:00.000 --> 1:06:01.840
Deciding the fate of a child

1:06:01.840 --> 1:06:04.840
is always
a very difficult decision.

1:06:04.840 --> 1:06:07.320
Now, I have no doubt
about the love

1:06:07.320 --> 1:06:10.160
between Mr. Coleridge
and his granddaughter,

1:06:10.160 --> 1:06:13.160
but I cannot ignore the facts
in front of me.

1:06:14.920 --> 1:06:17.440
[Judge Swanson]
I hereby grant temporary custody

1:06:17.440 --> 1:06:20.200
to Mr. and Mrs. Williams,

1:06:20.200 --> 1:06:22.000
pending further investigation
and of course

1:06:22.000 --> 1:06:23.520
a full review
by the court.

1:06:23.520 --> 1:06:24.760
No!

1:06:24.760 --> 1:06:27.640
[Judge Swanson]
Sit down, Mr. Coleridge.

1:06:27.640 --> 1:06:28.760
You can't take her away
from me.

1:06:28.760 --> 1:06:30.200
This is wrong!

1:06:30.200 --> 1:06:31.040
She's family!

1:06:31.040 --> 1:06:32.040
Oh, Jonah, please,

1:06:32.040 --> 1:06:34.080
don't make this harder
for Annabel.

1:06:34.080 --> 1:06:35.800
-You are not taking her!
-Bailiff.

1:06:35.800 --> 1:06:36.920
I need a bailiff in here.

1:06:36.920 --> 1:06:39.360
-Anna, we are going.
-Jonah, please.

1:06:39.360 --> 1:06:41.640
Oh, you're not takin' her
anywhere.

1:06:41.640 --> 1:06:44.120
You no longer have
legal custody.

1:06:44.120 --> 1:06:46.320
I told you not to mess with me.

1:06:48.320 --> 1:06:49.200
[grunting]

1:06:49.200 --> 1:06:50.360
Oh!

1:06:50.360 --> 1:06:51.760
Jonah, stop it!

1:06:51.760 --> 1:06:53.040
[Desaray]
Jonah, please!

1:06:53.040 --> 1:07:00.680
[♪♪♪]

1:07:00.680 --> 1:07:03.680
[sobbing]

1:07:06.080 --> 1:07:26.120
[♪♪♪]

1:07:27.400 --> 1:07:28.640
I'm sorry, Ms. Johnson,

1:07:28.640 --> 1:07:31.000
I won't be able to help you
with the tourist rush.

1:07:31.000 --> 1:07:32.240
Annabel, you'll never know

1:07:32.240 --> 1:07:33.680
how much we're gonna miss you,
honey.

1:07:33.680 --> 1:07:34.680
[sobbing]

1:07:34.680 --> 1:07:36.240
Miss you.

1:07:40.720 --> 1:07:43.600
[crying]

1:07:43.600 --> 1:07:54.400
[♪♪♪]

1:07:54.400 --> 1:07:56.320
Please look after gramps for me,
okay?

1:07:56.320 --> 1:07:57.720
[sobbing]

1:07:57.720 --> 1:07:59.200
Okay?

1:07:59.200 --> 1:08:02.200
[sobbing]

1:08:05.440 --> 1:08:08.440
You promise
to stay out of trouble, okay?

1:08:08.440 --> 1:08:09.840
I will.

1:08:09.840 --> 1:08:11.560
[sobbing]

1:08:11.560 --> 1:08:13.880
I want you
to take this with you.

1:08:13.880 --> 1:08:15.440
Your dad's hat?

1:08:15.440 --> 1:08:17.560
Keep it for me until I come
and visit you.

1:08:17.560 --> 1:08:20.560
[sobbing]

1:08:20.560 --> 1:08:30.160
[♪♪♪]

1:08:30.160 --> 1:08:32.000
You're gonna be fine, girl.

1:08:32.000 --> 1:08:32.840
You'll be alright.

1:08:32.840 --> 1:08:35.160
You'll-- you'll enjoy New York.

1:08:35.160 --> 1:08:38.160
[crying]

1:08:38.160 --> 1:08:52.920
[♪♪♪]

1:08:52.920 --> 1:08:54.200
Anna, we should go.

1:08:54.200 --> 1:08:57.200
[crying]

1:08:57.200 --> 1:09:10.520
[♪♪♪]

1:09:10.520 --> 1:09:13.320
I won't forget about you, Mitzy.

1:09:13.320 --> 1:09:15.480
I love you.

1:09:17.640 --> 1:09:20.640
There's no point
in making a fuss now.

1:09:20.640 --> 1:09:23.200
You're only
making everything harder!

1:09:23.200 --> 1:09:31.480
[♪♪♪]

1:09:31.480 --> 1:09:33.680
[sobbing]

1:09:33.680 --> 1:09:53.720
[♪♪♪]

1:09:53.720 --> 1:10:13.720
[♪♪♪]

1:10:23.400 --> 1:10:26.120
[Desaray]
I've been looking
for you everywhere.

1:10:26.120 --> 1:10:28.560
I spoke with my supervisor

1:10:28.560 --> 1:10:30.400
and she says if we can find
another social worker

1:10:30.400 --> 1:10:33.400
to review your case,
after further documentation,

1:10:33.400 --> 1:10:36.440
we can get my official report
reinstated.

1:10:36.440 --> 1:10:39.040
Do you know what you are?

1:10:39.040 --> 1:10:40.720
[chuckles]

1:10:40.720 --> 1:10:43.000
You're a hurricane.

1:10:43.000 --> 1:10:46.000
Hurricane Desaray.

1:10:46.000 --> 1:10:47.200
We were just living our lives.

1:10:47.200 --> 1:10:49.280
It was all fine.

1:10:49.280 --> 1:10:50.360
And then you blew in

1:10:50.360 --> 1:10:53.360
and turned everything
into broken things.

1:10:56.080 --> 1:10:59.080
That's all we are now.

1:10:59.080 --> 1:11:01.880
Just broken things waiting
on the beach

1:11:01.880 --> 1:11:03.720
waiting for the tide
to wash us away.

1:11:03.720 --> 1:11:05.320
I didn't mean
for any of it to happen.

1:11:05.320 --> 1:11:07.320
-I--
-No, hurricanes never do.

1:11:09.160 --> 1:11:12.160
They just blow in and blow out.

1:11:12.160 --> 1:11:13.360
There's nothing personal.

1:11:13.360 --> 1:11:15.920
They don't mean any harm,
but if you get in theior path

1:11:17.040 --> 1:11:20.040
Jonah, please least look at me.

1:11:20.040 --> 1:11:22.000
Please.

1:11:25.920 --> 1:11:27.640
Storm's over, Desaray.

1:11:30.360 --> 1:11:32.640
I haven't got anything more
for you to blow away.

1:11:32.640 --> 1:11:44.120
[♪♪♪]

1:11:44.120 --> 1:11:46.640
Here are your tickets
and documents needed

1:11:46.640 --> 1:11:48.360
for your trip back
to New York.

1:11:48.360 --> 1:11:50.120
Uh, I'll follow up
with any additional paperwork

1:11:50.120 --> 1:11:51.400
you might need.

1:11:51.400 --> 1:11:53.960
Is there anything else I can do
to be of service?

1:11:53.960 --> 1:11:55.320
No.

1:11:55.320 --> 1:11:58.320
you've done everything I asked
very efficiently, Mr. Carbunkle.

1:11:58.320 --> 1:12:00.960
[Carbunkle]
Well, we do aim to please, sir.

1:12:00.960 --> 1:12:02.800
And I hope
you'll keep me in mind

1:12:02.800 --> 1:12:05.800
for your future legal needs
or anything else

1:12:05.800 --> 1:12:08.440
I can do
to be of service.

1:12:08.440 --> 1:12:10.080
We should get to the airport.

1:12:10.080 --> 1:12:12.440
[Desaray]
You're not going anywhere!

1:12:12.440 --> 1:12:14.160
How dare you try
and take way this girl

1:12:14.160 --> 1:12:15.800
from all the people
who love her.

1:12:15.800 --> 1:12:16.960
Ms. Rolle,
this is not the time for--

1:12:16.960 --> 1:12:18.400
I'm not talking to you,

1:12:18.400 --> 1:12:21.400
you dirty, lying, cheating,
conniving,

1:12:21.400 --> 1:12:23.520
weird pirate!

1:12:23.520 --> 1:12:24.840
Weird?

1:12:24.840 --> 1:12:27.120
This is between me
and these people.

1:12:28.280 --> 1:12:30.160
This is none of your business.

1:12:30.160 --> 1:12:31.680
[Sam]
We're doing what's best
for our granddaughter.

1:12:31.680 --> 1:12:33.400
[Desaray]
No, you're not!

1:12:33.400 --> 1:12:35.000
You are doing what's best
for you

1:12:35.000 --> 1:12:36.400
and I'm sure
that's all you've ever done

1:12:36.400 --> 1:12:39.120
your entire privileged lives!

1:12:39.120 --> 1:12:40.800
[Desaray]
All you have to do
is look at Annabel

1:12:40.800 --> 1:12:42.240
to see that she's heartbroken.

1:12:42.240 --> 1:12:44.480
You're doing this because you--

1:12:44.480 --> 1:12:47.480
you pushed your daughter away
all those years ago,

1:12:47.480 --> 1:12:48.960
and now she's gone,

1:12:48.960 --> 1:12:51.000
and there's nothing you can do
to bring her back.

1:12:51.000 --> 1:12:52.880
[Desaray]
Nothing.

1:12:52.880 --> 1:12:55.560
Certainly not torturing
this young girl

1:12:55.560 --> 1:12:58.040
and the man
who's dedicated his life

1:12:58.040 --> 1:13:01.040
to taking care of her the way
your daughter wanted him to.

1:13:02.840 --> 1:13:05.880
Samuel, this has gone too far.

1:13:05.880 --> 1:13:07.880
Sheryl,
we discussed all of this.

1:13:07.880 --> 1:13:10.680
If we want to be part
of her life,

1:13:10.680 --> 1:13:13.720
we should move here
and be a part of her life,

1:13:13.720 --> 1:13:16.720
not force her into ours.

1:13:16.720 --> 1:13:19.160
That was what we did to Debrah.

1:13:19.160 --> 1:13:21.600
Let's not make
that mistake again.

1:13:23.200 --> 1:13:24.720
I don't know anymore.

1:13:24.720 --> 1:13:25.520
[chuckles]

1:13:25.520 --> 1:13:26.840
Mr. Williams,

1:13:26.840 --> 1:13:28.600
You're not actually taking
this woman seriously, are you?

1:13:28.600 --> 1:13:30.880
No, you did not just
put your hand in my face.

1:13:30.880 --> 1:13:32.440
And what if I did?

1:13:32.440 --> 1:13:34.840
[grunts]

1:13:34.840 --> 1:13:36.200
Anna?

1:13:36.200 --> 1:13:37.360
Anna?

1:13:37.360 --> 1:13:39.320
Anna?

1:13:41.160 --> 1:13:42.080
[sighs]

1:13:42.080 --> 1:13:43.320
Annabel!

1:13:43.320 --> 1:13:45.200
Huh.

1:13:45.200 --> 1:13:47.040
[sighing]

1:13:47.040 --> 1:13:48.320
What is she doing?

1:13:48.320 --> 1:13:50.160
I'd guess running away.

1:13:50.160 --> 1:13:51.520
Why would she do that?

1:13:51.520 --> 1:13:52.880
You really don't have a clue,
do you?

1:13:52.880 --> 1:13:54.080
Well, where would she go?

1:13:54.080 --> 1:13:55.320
Anywhere.

1:13:55.320 --> 1:13:58.080
She knows this island
like the back of her hand.

1:13:58.080 --> 1:14:00.480
We need to get some help.

1:14:00.480 --> 1:14:01.520
What can we do?

1:14:01.520 --> 1:14:04.480
[takes a deep breath]

1:14:04.480 --> 1:14:06.480
There's a restaurant
on the leeway side of the island

1:14:06.480 --> 1:14:07.920
called "Coconuts".

1:14:07.920 --> 1:14:10.520
Its' owned by a woman
named "Grace Johnson".

1:14:10.520 --> 1:14:12.360
Go there
and tell her what happened!

1:14:12.360 --> 1:14:13.280
I'll get Jonah.

1:14:13.280 --> 1:14:14.280
-Right.
-Okay.

1:14:14.280 --> 1:14:15.240
That woman assaulted me.

1:14:15.240 --> 1:14:16.560
That was assault!

1:14:16.560 --> 1:14:17.280
You saw it.

1:14:17.280 --> 1:14:18.120
They were witnesses.

1:14:18.120 --> 1:14:19.200
I will sue!

1:14:19.200 --> 1:14:21.920
Shut up!

1:14:21.920 --> 1:14:23.640
Did you hear what she said
to me?

1:14:23.640 --> 1:14:25.120
-Mr. Carbunkle.
-Yes, sir?

1:14:25.120 --> 1:14:26.640
Shut up!

1:14:28.240 --> 1:14:30.920
Unbelievable!

1:14:30.920 --> 1:14:32.080
[scoffs]

1:14:32.080 --> 1:14:39.800
[♪♪♪]

1:14:39.800 --> 1:14:41.080
I've been out here all week.

1:14:41.080 --> 1:14:42.800
Look, I'm just tryin'
to get a hold of this boat,

1:14:42.800 --> 1:14:44.680
I wanna go, I wanna have
a good time in the ocean,

1:14:44.680 --> 1:14:45.560
you know?

1:14:45.560 --> 1:14:46.560
[tourist]
I can't just--

1:14:46.560 --> 1:14:48.680
How much longer
is this gonna take?

1:14:48.680 --> 1:14:51.320
[boat owner]
I need to replace the fuel pump,
change the batteries.

1:14:51.320 --> 1:14:53.840
I think it should be done
in a couple of hours.

1:14:59.680 --> 1:15:02.160
Hey, what are you doing?

1:15:02.160 --> 1:15:03.160
Hey, hey, hey!

1:15:03.160 --> 1:15:04.520
We need your help.

1:15:04.520 --> 1:15:06.000
What are you two doin' here?

1:15:06.000 --> 1:15:07.520
[Sheryl]
No, no, it's Anna.

1:15:07.520 --> 1:15:08.600
She's run away.

1:15:08.600 --> 1:15:10.040
-What?
-[Sam] She's gone!

1:15:10.040 --> 1:15:12.000
-She's disappeared!
-Okay, alright, everyone quiet!

1:15:12.000 --> 1:15:12.960
Okay, when did she go?

1:15:12.960 --> 1:15:13.960
About half an hour ago.

1:15:13.960 --> 1:15:15.160
Maybe longer.

1:15:15.160 --> 1:15:16.440
Well, she couldn't have gotten
far.

1:15:16.440 --> 1:15:18.760
Um, Will and Megan,
you're gonna check the marina

1:15:18.760 --> 1:15:20.000
and Jonah's fish stand, okay?

1:15:20.000 --> 1:15:21.160
-James--
-Yeah.

1:15:21.160 --> 1:15:22.440
Check the local piers
and Lighthouse Bay.

1:15:22.440 --> 1:15:23.440
Okay.

1:15:23.440 --> 1:15:24.640
Arthur,
just call everyone you know

1:15:24.640 --> 1:15:25.440
and have them lookin', okay?

1:15:25.440 --> 1:15:26.400
Right away.

1:15:26.400 --> 1:15:27.560
Everyone else just come with me,
alright?

1:15:27.560 --> 1:15:28.160
Wait.

1:15:28.160 --> 1:15:29.000
What can we do?

1:15:29.000 --> 1:15:30.560
Haven't you two done enough?

1:15:30.560 --> 1:15:31.440
Stop.

1:15:31.440 --> 1:15:32.480
Listen, that's their blood.

1:15:32.480 --> 1:15:33.720
Okay, you two,
you're gonna come with me,

1:15:33.720 --> 1:15:35.000
alright?

1:15:35.000 --> 1:15:36.000
What is everyone standing for?

1:15:36.000 --> 1:15:36.840
Let's go!

1:15:36.840 --> 1:15:37.440
Yeah, let's go!

1:15:37.440 --> 1:15:38.720
Go, go.

1:15:38.720 --> 1:15:40.000
[grunting]

1:15:40.000 --> 1:15:54.320
[♪♪♪]

1:15:54.320 --> 1:15:55.720
[Desaray]
Jonah!

1:15:55.720 --> 1:15:56.760
Jonah.

1:15:56.760 --> 1:15:57.760
Desaray, I told you I can't--

1:15:57.760 --> 1:15:59.360
It's Annabel!

1:15:59.360 --> 1:16:02.360
-I don't wanna talk about Anna-- -Annabel's missing!

1:16:03.680 --> 1:16:06.440
She's run away
and no one knows where she is.

1:16:07.440 --> 1:16:09.160
well, we need to get help.

1:16:09.160 --> 1:16:11.640
The Williams went to tell Grace.

1:16:11.640 --> 1:16:13.040
Well, we have to check
her school

1:16:13.040 --> 1:16:15.760
and the marina,
and her friends.

1:16:15.760 --> 1:16:17.400
Come on!

1:16:17.400 --> 1:16:37.400
[♪♪♪]

1:16:37.400 --> 1:16:57.440
[♪♪♪]

1:16:57.440 --> 1:17:07.240
[♪♪♪]

1:17:07.240 --> 1:17:10.000
Ugh, what's wrong with it?

1:17:10.000 --> 1:17:12.440
[grunting]

1:17:13.560 --> 1:17:16.400
Mayday, mayday,
this is Annabel Coleridge,

1:17:16.400 --> 1:17:19.000
approximately 5 miles
in North North East

1:17:19.000 --> 1:17:21.000
of Lighthouse Bay.

1:17:21.000 --> 1:17:23.280
Uh, do you read?

1:17:23.280 --> 1:17:24.120
Oh, great.

1:17:24.120 --> 1:17:25.120
I have a dead radio.

1:17:25.120 --> 1:17:26.120
[sighs]

1:17:26.120 --> 1:17:28.000
And no life jackets.

1:17:28.000 --> 1:17:48.000
[♪♪♪]

1:17:52.280 --> 1:17:54.160
Mitzy, am I glad to see you!

1:17:56.320 --> 1:17:59.320
I know, this wasn't a good idea,
but now is not the time.

1:17:59.320 --> 1:18:00.600
I need help.

1:18:00.600 --> 1:18:02.280
Do you understand?

1:18:05.920 --> 1:18:07.120
Take this to grampa.

1:18:07.120 --> 1:18:08.040
Do you understand?

1:18:08.040 --> 1:18:09.880
Home, Mitzy!

1:18:09.880 --> 1:18:11.600
Grandpa!

1:18:11.600 --> 1:18:18.640
[♪♪♪]

1:18:18.640 --> 1:18:20.720
Hurry, girl, hurry!

1:18:23.880 --> 1:18:25.880
[Jonah]
She's nowhere in the center.

1:18:25.880 --> 1:18:27.760
And she didn't come back here.

1:18:27.760 --> 1:18:29.040
[Desaray sighing]

1:18:29.040 --> 1:18:30.760
Jonah, there's no sign of her.

1:18:30.760 --> 1:18:31.640
I'm so sorry.

1:18:31.640 --> 1:18:32.480
[sighs]

1:18:32.480 --> 1:18:33.480
James, anything?

1:18:33.480 --> 1:18:34.760
Nothin', Jonah, nothin'.

1:18:34.760 --> 1:18:36.480
-Will, Megan?
-We checked everywhere.

1:18:36.480 --> 1:18:38.360
No one's seen her.

1:18:39.480 --> 1:18:40.520
[sighing]

1:18:40.520 --> 1:18:41.720
Where can she be?

1:18:41.720 --> 1:18:43.640
It's like the girl
just evaporated.

1:18:43.640 --> 1:18:49.920
[♪♪♪]

1:18:49.920 --> 1:18:52.040
Maybe we should call the police.

1:18:54.800 --> 1:18:55.960
Mitzy, stop!

1:18:55.960 --> 1:18:57.560
Just stop it.

1:19:00.920 --> 1:19:02.920
Uh, listen um, have you tried
the grocery store?

1:19:02.920 --> 1:19:04.080
Did anyone see here there?

1:19:04.080 --> 1:19:05.480
[indistinct conversation]

1:19:05.480 --> 1:19:06.640
-Are there no boats?
-No, no boats.

1:19:06.640 --> 1:19:07.560
You sure?

1:19:07.560 --> 1:19:08.560
You checked them all?

1:19:08.560 --> 1:19:11.560
[indistinct conversation]

1:19:13.840 --> 1:19:15.800
What's it got in its mouth?

1:19:15.800 --> 1:19:29.240
[♪♪♪]

1:19:29.240 --> 1:19:31.000
Mom, I think Mitzy knows
where Annabel is!

1:19:31.000 --> 1:19:32.400
-Oh, Mateo.
-Look!

1:19:32.400 --> 1:19:33.360
What is it?

1:19:33.360 --> 1:19:34.200
It's my hat!

1:19:34.200 --> 1:19:35.400
I gave it to her
before she left.

1:19:35.400 --> 1:19:38.240
She was wearing it this morning.

1:19:38.240 --> 1:19:41.000
Mitzy.

1:19:41.000 --> 1:19:42.720
Mitzy!

1:19:45.800 --> 1:19:48.120
Can you show us where Anna is?

1:19:49.240 --> 1:19:50.280
Are you sure?

1:19:50.280 --> 1:19:51.680
Is that even possible?

1:19:55.040 --> 1:19:56.160
It's worth a try.

1:19:56.160 --> 1:19:57.160
Come on!

1:19:57.160 --> 1:19:58.280
[taking deep breaths]

1:19:58.280 --> 1:20:00.720
Will, undo my boat lines!

1:20:00.720 --> 1:20:08.720
[♪♪♪]

1:20:08.720 --> 1:20:10.720
Sam!

1:20:10.720 --> 1:20:12.720
Sheryl!

1:20:14.400 --> 1:20:16.040
Come on.

1:20:16.040 --> 1:20:36.080
[♪♪♪]

1:20:36.080 --> 1:20:48.560
[♪♪♪]

1:20:48.560 --> 1:20:51.280
I hope you're proud of yourself.

1:20:51.280 --> 1:21:10.040
[♪♪♪]

1:21:10.040 --> 1:21:12.240
Judge Swanson?

1:21:12.240 --> 1:21:15.040
It's Robert Carbunkle
calling about the report.

1:21:15.040 --> 1:21:16.040
[clears throat]

1:21:16.040 --> 1:21:18.360
Yes, sir,
I have a confession to make.

1:21:18.360 --> 1:21:29.520
[♪♪♪]

1:21:29.520 --> 1:21:31.120
Mateo, go forward.

1:21:31.120 --> 1:21:33.080
Standby to let go the anchor.

1:21:33.080 --> 1:21:34.920
Yes, sir.

1:21:34.920 --> 1:21:41.840
[♪♪♪]

1:21:41.840 --> 1:21:43.800
[taking deep breaths]

1:21:43.800 --> 1:21:45.960
Any sign of Annabel?

1:21:45.960 --> 1:21:46.800
Not yet.

1:21:50.080 --> 1:21:52.560
Well, it looks like Mitzy knows
where she's going.

1:21:53.680 --> 1:21:55.160
Yes, I hope so.

1:21:55.160 --> 1:22:02.280
[♪♪♪]

1:22:02.280 --> 1:22:03.240
I see her.

1:22:03.240 --> 1:22:05.000
-Okay!
-I see her.

1:22:05.000 --> 1:22:06.400
Oh, there she is!

1:22:06.400 --> 1:22:08.400
There she is.

1:22:10.000 --> 1:22:12.840
Mateo, is she on the boat?

1:22:12.840 --> 1:22:14.280
I think so.

1:22:14.280 --> 1:22:28.000
[♪♪♪]

1:22:28.000 --> 1:22:29.880
I got you.

1:22:29.880 --> 1:22:31.720
Yeah, hang on, sweetheart,
I got you.

1:22:34.440 --> 1:22:35.680
[Gasping]

1:22:35.680 --> 1:22:38.560
[sighing]

1:22:38.560 --> 1:22:39.560
Anna.

1:22:39.560 --> 1:22:56.760
[♪♪♪]

1:22:56.760 --> 1:22:58.320
Mateo, let go the anchor!

1:22:58.320 --> 1:23:00.160
Yeah!

1:23:05.320 --> 1:23:06.160
Can you see her?

1:23:06.160 --> 1:23:08.280
No.

1:23:08.280 --> 1:23:20.440
[♪♪♪]

1:23:20.440 --> 1:23:23.000
Jonah, I see Mitzy!

1:23:23.000 --> 1:23:25.440
I'm not sure where Anna is.

1:23:25.440 --> 1:23:27.600
Mateo, take this,
get up on the roof.

1:23:27.600 --> 1:23:29.480
Go, go!

